00:56.623 --> 01:00.150
This is a true story about friendship
that runs deeper than blood.

01:01.361 --> 01:04.194
This is my story and that of
the only three friends in my life...

01:04.263 --> 01:06.732
who truly mattered.

01:06.800 --> 01:11.134
Two of them were killers
who never made it past the age of 30.

01:11.204 --> 01:14.935
The other is a nonpracticing attorney
living with the pain of his past...

01:15.008 --> 01:18.444
too afraid to let it go,
never confronting its horror.

01:20.080 --> 01:24.312
I'm the only one who can speak for them
and the children we were.

03:00.713 --> 03:04.513
<i>Walk, walk</i>
<i>Walk, walk</i>

03:05.518 --> 03:07.713
My three friends and I
were inseparable...

03:07.787 --> 03:10.722
happy and content to live
in the closed world of Hell's Kitchen.

03:10.790 --> 03:14.123
The West Side streets of Manhattan
were our private playground.

03:14.194 --> 03:18.494
A cement kingdom where we felt ourselves
to be nothing less than absolute rulers.

03:20.900 --> 03:24.392
Hell's Kitchen was populated
by an uneasy blend of Irish, Italian...

03:24.470 --> 03:27.098
Puerto Rican
and Eastern European laborers.

03:27.173 --> 03:29.164
Hard men living hard lives.

03:29.242 --> 03:31.073
Move it!

03:32.078 --> 03:33.739
<i>He said</i>

03:33.813 --> 03:37.112
<i>Walk like a man</i>
<i>Talk like a man</i>

03:37.183 --> 03:39.174
Shut the fuck up!

03:39.252 --> 03:42.585
We lived in railroad apartments
inside redbrick tenements.

03:42.655 --> 03:45.624
Few mothers worked and all had
trouble with the men they married.

03:45.692 --> 03:48.024
Get the fuck down and shut up!

03:48.094 --> 03:49.755
Get the fuck down!

03:49.829 --> 03:52.593
Get the fuck down
and shut the fuck up!

03:52.665 --> 03:55.327
I buried one fucking wife,
I can bury another one.

04:01.441 --> 04:04.433
Domestic violence was
a cottage industry in Hell's Kitchen...

04:04.510 --> 04:07.445
yet there was no divorce
and few separations.

04:07.513 --> 04:09.447
The will of the church was forceful.

04:09.515 --> 04:12.507
For a marriage to end,
someone usually had to die.

04:15.488 --> 04:17.456
Yet despite the harshness of life...

04:17.523 --> 04:20.617
Hell's Kitchen offered
the kids on its streets a safety net...

04:20.692 --> 04:23.491
enjoyed by few other neighborhoods.

04:23.563 --> 04:26.191
Crimes against people of the
neighborhood were not permitted.

04:27.100 --> 04:29.796
When they did occur,
the punishment doled out was severe...

04:29.869 --> 04:32.064
and in some cases final.

04:32.138 --> 04:34.129
A drug dealer from
an uptown neighborhood...

04:34.207 --> 04:36.141
moved heroin into Hell's Kitchen.

04:36.209 --> 04:39.235
Packet killed the 12-year-old son
of a Puerto Rican numbers runner.

04:39.312 --> 04:42.110
It was the last packet
the dealer ever sold.

04:43.116 --> 04:47.018
Hell's Kitchen was a place of innocence
ruled by corruption.

04:49.322 --> 04:52.291
My friends and I spent lots of time
inside Holy Angels.

04:52.358 --> 04:54.588
We each served as altar boys.

04:54.661 --> 04:56.595
Everyone wanted
to work funeral masses...

04:56.663 --> 04:58.722
since the funeral
included a $3 fee...

04:58.798 --> 05:01.289
and more if you looked
sufficiently somber.

05:02.869 --> 05:05.201
There was an active competition
between the four of us...

05:05.271 --> 05:08.263
to come up with
the best and boldest prank.

05:08.341 --> 05:11.003
Two weeks into the new school year
I found the nuns' clacker...

05:11.077 --> 05:13.739
in the school hallway,
and I was ready for the big leagues.

05:13.813 --> 05:16.077
l... I'm very pleased that so many
boys and girls are going to...

05:16.149 --> 05:18.140
In church it was used
to alert the girls as to when...

05:18.217 --> 05:20.481
they should stand,
sit, kneel and genuflect...

05:20.553 --> 05:23.488
all based on the number of times
a clacker was pressed.

05:23.556 --> 05:26.423
In my pocket, it was cause for havoc.

05:27.527 --> 05:31.395
And, uh, it will be a great day.

05:35.735 --> 05:38.226
You will be defenders of the faith...

05:38.304 --> 05:40.602
you will be soldiers of Christ...

05:40.673 --> 05:42.732
and you will receive the gifts...

05:42.809 --> 05:44.936
of the Holy Spirit.

05:50.917 --> 05:53.385
Well, it's gonna be a great day...

05:53.453 --> 05:55.387
and your parents
will be very proud of you.

05:55.455 --> 05:58.720
When you were baptized,
godparents made promises for you...

05:58.791 --> 06:00.725
and now you're gonna
confirm those promises.

06:00.793 --> 06:02.658
Let me have the clacker.

06:02.729 --> 06:05.459
- What clacker?
- Now.

06:05.531 --> 06:07.726
Let everyone rise.

06:10.803 --> 06:12.566
Let us pray.

06:21.381 --> 06:23.713
Nuns are such easy targets.

06:25.318 --> 06:27.980
John and I spent more time
in church than the others.

06:28.054 --> 06:30.887
We were the only two of the group
to give any thought of entering
the priesthood.

06:30.957 --> 06:33.619
And John and I were intrigued
by the powers a priest was given.

06:33.693 --> 06:35.684
A secret world of betrayal
and deceit...

06:35.762 --> 06:38.993
where people openly admitted
dark misdeeds and vile indiscretions.

06:39.065 --> 06:41.556
Confession was better than any book
we could get our hands on...

06:41.634 --> 06:44.467
or any movie we could see,
because the sins were real...

06:44.537 --> 06:46.528
committed by people we knew.

06:46.606 --> 06:49.097
The temptation to be part of that
was far too great to resist.

06:49.175 --> 06:51.370
If we get caught, they'll burn us.

06:51.444 --> 06:53.378
What if our mothers are out there?

06:53.446 --> 06:55.880
What if we end up
hearing their confessions?

06:55.948 --> 06:58.781
- Yeah, what if we hear something worse?
- Like what?

06:58.851 --> 07:00.842
Like a murder.

07:00.920 --> 07:03.013
What if somebody
cops to a murder?

07:03.089 --> 07:06.991
Relax. All we gotta do is sit back,
listen, and remember not to laugh.

07:11.697 --> 07:13.858
Hide.

07:14.867 --> 07:17.768
Seconds later,
our booth comes to life.

07:17.837 --> 07:20.829
l, uh, sleep with married men.

07:21.841 --> 07:23.809
Men with families.

07:24.510 --> 07:28.674
In the morning I tell myself
it's the last time, but it never is.

07:31.250 --> 07:33.241
Yes?

07:33.319 --> 07:35.844
You see, I'm, uh...

07:35.922 --> 07:38.083
I'm pregnant.

07:40.359 --> 07:44.295
- The father?
- Huh, take a number.

07:44.363 --> 07:48.595
- What are you going to do?
- I know what you want me to do.

07:48.668 --> 07:51.432
And I know what I should do.

07:51.504 --> 07:54.496
I just don't know what I'm gonna do.

07:56.309 --> 07:58.402
Look, I gotta go.

07:58.478 --> 08:01.845
Thanks for listenin', fellas.
I really appreciated it.

08:01.914 --> 08:04.405
I know you'll keep it to yourselves.

08:10.389 --> 08:13.381
- She knew.
- Yeah, she knew.

08:13.459 --> 08:16.690
Why do you think she told us all that?

08:16.762 --> 08:19.754
I don't know.
I guess she had to tell somebody.

08:23.302 --> 08:25.600
Father Robert Carillo
was a longshoreman's son...

08:25.671 --> 08:28.868
who was as comfortable sitting
on a barstool in a back-alley saloon...

08:28.941 --> 08:31.603
as he was standing at the altar
during High Mass.

08:31.677 --> 08:34.840
He had toyed with the life of petty
crime before finding his calling.

08:34.914 --> 08:37.381
He was a friend. A friend
who just happened to be a priest.

08:37.450 --> 08:39.645
You know what crap like that
does to your body?

08:39.719 --> 08:43.052
Come on, Father. It beats smoking,
and it's cheaper too.

08:43.121 --> 08:45.147
Maybe.

08:45.224 --> 08:48.523
- So what do you hear? Anything?
- No, nothin'.

08:48.594 --> 08:50.585
I hear you're interested
in becomin' a priest.

08:50.663 --> 08:52.631
Who says?

08:52.698 --> 08:55.360
Word is, you wanna get the feel
of a confessional booth.

08:55.434 --> 08:57.959
I don't know
what you're talking about, Father.

08:58.037 --> 09:00.028
- You don't, huh?
- No.

09:00.106 --> 09:02.097
Well, maybe I got
the wrong information.

09:02.174 --> 09:04.369
Yeah, I guess you did.

09:04.443 --> 09:06.377
I'll see you later tonight.

09:06.445 --> 09:08.276
What's tonight?

09:08.347 --> 09:10.474
I gotta drop some books
and magazines off...

09:10.550 --> 09:12.711
for the elderly and disabled
around the neighborhood.

09:12.785 --> 09:16.414
- Your mother said you'd love to help.
- Yeah, I bet she did.

09:18.324 --> 09:22.055
Shakes, I don't want you
getting into any trouble.

09:22.128 --> 09:24.460
Come on, Father.
You know I never do.

09:24.530 --> 09:26.794
That's all I wish
for you and your friends.

09:26.866 --> 09:28.857
- That's it?
- That's it. Nothing else. I swear.

09:28.935 --> 09:31.733
- That's it.
- You know, a priest shouldn't swear.

09:31.804 --> 09:34.272
And kids shouldn't be listening
to other people's confessions.

09:34.340 --> 09:36.331
- I'll see you tonight.
- All right. See you.

09:36.409 --> 09:38.104
Okay.

09:40.813 --> 09:43.304
Michael was the most sexually
experienced of our group...

09:43.382 --> 09:46.283
which meant that he kissed a girl
on more than one occasion.

09:46.352 --> 09:48.980
But his real love was Carol Martinez.

09:49.055 --> 09:51.580
Hell's Kitchen's half-breed...
half Puerto Rican, half Irish.

09:51.657 --> 09:55.252
She was raised by her father,
her mother having died at childbirth.

09:55.328 --> 09:59.628
Carol stayed pretty much to herself, but
was always comfortable in our company.

09:59.699 --> 10:01.690
We could always count on Carol
to stand sentry...

10:01.767 --> 10:03.735
on the first night of the Ice Capades.

10:03.803 --> 10:05.794
While crowds of families
lined the front of the Garden...

10:05.871 --> 10:07.839
waiting to see the skaters perform...

10:07.907 --> 10:09.670
we each had one eye in a hole...

10:09.742 --> 10:11.767
watching two dozen beautiful,
nearly naked women...

10:11.844 --> 10:13.835
get into their skaters' outfits.

10:16.749 --> 10:19.217
This is what heaven must be about.

10:19.285 --> 10:23.381
<i>Good, good, good, good vibrations</i>

10:23.456 --> 10:25.287
Oh, my God!

10:27.460 --> 10:31.487
- Hey, uh, Carol, you wanna take a look?
- Like it's something I haven't seen.

10:32.498 --> 10:34.523
So lucky. Oh, wow.

10:34.600 --> 10:36.431
She's so beautiful.
Oh, my...

10:36.502 --> 10:39.665
I could die now,
and I wouldn't be sad.

10:39.739 --> 10:41.707
When my friends and I were young...

10:41.774 --> 10:44.766
Hell's Kitchen was run
by a man named King Benny.

10:44.844 --> 10:48.109
When he was young, King Benny
was a hit man for Lucky Luciano.

10:48.180 --> 10:51.274
Lucky Luciano did a lot of good
for this country during World War II...

10:51.350 --> 10:54.285
but you ain't gonna read about that
in any fucking history book.

10:54.353 --> 10:57.288
There was talk King Benny
was the shooter of Mad Dog Coll...

10:57.356 --> 10:59.756
that prick on West 23rd Street.

10:59.825 --> 11:01.759
He ran bootleg with Dutch Schultz...

11:01.827 --> 11:05.126
and he opened up a couple of clubs
with Tough Tony Anastasia.

11:05.197 --> 11:07.529
I was 14 when I first heard about him.

11:07.600 --> 11:11.593
The story goes, as a kid
he wasn't much of anything.

11:11.671 --> 11:14.299
He was always getting the shit
kicked out of him in street fights.

11:14.373 --> 11:16.898
And then one day...
and who the fuck knows why...

11:16.976 --> 11:20.173
some Irish guy about 25 years old...

11:20.246 --> 11:23.875
he takes King Benny and he flings him
down a flight of stairs.

11:23.949 --> 11:26.884
King Benny breaks
all his teeth in the front.

11:26.952 --> 11:29.546
You know what King Benny does?

11:29.622 --> 11:31.783
He waits.

11:31.857 --> 11:35.349
He waits eight years
to get even with that prick.

11:35.428 --> 11:39.364
He walks into a public bathhouse.
The guy's soaking in the tub.

11:39.432 --> 11:42.299
King Benny
takes out his front teeth.

11:42.368 --> 11:44.359
He lays 'em down on the sink.

11:45.504 --> 11:47.768
Then he looks over at the guy
and he says...

11:49.442 --> 11:53.572
"When I look in the mirror,
I see your face."

11:53.646 --> 11:55.705
Then he pulls out a gun...

11:56.449 --> 11:58.576
and he shoots the guy
twice in each leg.

11:58.651 --> 12:00.585
Bang! Bang!
Bang! Bang!

12:01.620 --> 12:03.611
Then he says to the guy...

12:03.689 --> 12:07.921
" Now when you take a bath
you see mine."

12:08.928 --> 12:12.420
No one ever fucked
with King Benny after that.

12:12.498 --> 12:14.557
Revenge.

12:15.301 --> 12:17.064
Revenge.

12:19.705 --> 12:21.798
Can I talk to you for a minute?

12:21.874 --> 12:25.503
I'd like to work for you,
help you out, whatever you need.

12:25.578 --> 12:27.910
You're the butcher's kid.
Am I right?

12:27.980 --> 12:29.948
- Yeah.
- Well...

12:30.015 --> 12:32.074
what kind of job
are you looking for?

12:32.151 --> 12:34.278
Whatever.
It doesn't matter.

12:34.353 --> 12:36.685
Oh, doesn't matter, huh?

12:37.857 --> 12:40.690
Everybody says this is the place
to come for jobs.

12:40.760 --> 12:43.661
- Who is "everybody"?
- People from the neighborhood.

12:43.729 --> 12:45.560
Oh, them.

12:45.631 --> 12:48.259
Let me ask you,
what the fuck do they know?

12:48.334 --> 12:50.996
They know you got jobs.

12:55.841 --> 12:58.674
Sorry I wasted your time.

12:58.744 --> 13:01.645
- Hold on a sec.
- Yeah?

13:01.714 --> 13:03.841
Come back tomorrow
if you wanna work.

13:03.916 --> 13:05.679
- What time tomorrow?
- Anytime.

13:05.751 --> 13:08.948
- You'll be here?
- I'm always here.

13:16.295 --> 13:18.456
My first job for King Benny
paid $25 a week...

13:18.531 --> 13:21.466
and ate up only 40 minutes
of my time.

13:21.534 --> 13:24.469
In the dark clubroom, one of the guys
would hand me a crumpled paper bag...

13:24.537 --> 13:27.734
and direct me to one of the two
local police precincts for delivery.

13:27.807 --> 13:29.798
Hey, it was a perfect way
to handle payouts.

13:29.875 --> 13:31.866
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Come on.

13:31.944 --> 13:35.345
Let's go. Right here. See what kind
of cash you got in that bag.

13:35.414 --> 13:37.575
You gotta be nuts.
You know who you're taking off?

13:37.650 --> 13:41.086
Yeah, we know,
and we're scared shitless.

13:41.153 --> 13:43.917
Give me the bag.
Give me the fucking bag!

13:43.989 --> 13:46.355
Hey, what you do there?

13:46.425 --> 13:48.689
- Answer me! What you do there?
- Relax.

13:48.761 --> 13:51.924
- They stopped me and took my money.
- You took the money from the boy?

13:51.997 --> 13:54.022
- The money they took is in the bag.
- Let me have the bag.

13:54.099 --> 13:57.330
- Fuck you!
- Oh, yeah? How about now?

13:57.403 --> 14:00.236
- All right, all right, take it easy.
- Ah, you're not smart anymore.

14:00.306 --> 14:02.297
- Take it easy.
- Now you... This make you stupid.

14:02.374 --> 14:04.365
Let me have the bag.

14:05.377 --> 14:07.868
All right. Thanks, kid.
Now go.

14:07.947 --> 14:09.778
- What about them?
- You care?

14:09.849 --> 14:12.079
- No.
- Then go! Go! Run!

14:13.919 --> 14:17.116
I need somebody with me.
What if the old guy hadn't shown?

14:17.189 --> 14:19.783
- What you need?
- My friends.

14:19.859 --> 14:22.521
Your friends?
What do you think, this is camp?

14:22.595 --> 14:25.928
These kids you can trust.
I've known 'em half my life.

14:27.433 --> 14:29.924
Okay, get your friends.

14:30.002 --> 14:31.993
Father Bobby knew my friends and I
worked for King Benny...

14:32.071 --> 14:33.732
and he wasn't pleased.

14:33.806 --> 14:36.502
He wasn't worried about
the pocket money, but the next step...

14:36.575 --> 14:38.736
when they ask you to pick up a gun.

14:38.811 --> 14:40.802
He didn't want that to happen to us.

14:40.880 --> 14:42.871
You think running for King Benny
is a good idea, huh?

14:42.948 --> 14:44.939
- It pays.
- Pays? A lot of things pay.

14:45.017 --> 14:48.282
Not like this.
Whoa!

14:48.354 --> 14:50.822
Most priests liked to preach
from the pulpit.

14:50.890 --> 14:54.986
Father Bobby liked to talk during
the bump and shove of a pickup game.

14:55.060 --> 14:57.927
- Oh, good shot!
- All right, you the man.

14:57.997 --> 15:01.364
- I found an art class for you to take.
- You know I can't afford
to take any art classes.

15:01.433 --> 15:04.266
No, you don't have to pay anything.
Teacher's a friend of mine. Hmm?

15:04.336 --> 15:07.567
- I don't know. It could be
nothing but a waste of time, Father.
- Maybe.

15:07.640 --> 15:11.235
- Or it could be the first step.
- First step to what?
- To doing somethin' with your life.

15:11.310 --> 15:12.709
You never know.
It may help you get out of here.

15:12.778 --> 15:15.508
- You all could get out of here.
- Guys, are we gonna talk
or play basketball?

15:15.581 --> 15:17.515
Come on. Let's play.

15:18.517 --> 15:21.509
- Listen, I got a story I wanna tell you.
- It ain't the one about
the lepers, is it?

15:21.587 --> 15:24.420
- 'Cause that one gave me nightmares.
- No lepers. Michelangelo.

15:24.490 --> 15:27.823
He was born poor just like you guys.
He was a painter. He was a sculptor.

15:27.893 --> 15:31.294
He takes this job from the pope.
Good money, good work.

15:32.531 --> 15:34.590
Okay, Father, but, uh,
why'd the pope call him?

15:34.667 --> 15:36.760
Because the pope was looking
for the best guy he could find...

15:36.835 --> 15:38.826
to paint the ceiling
of his church in Rome.

15:38.904 --> 15:42.340
- Don't sound like
that big a job, Father.
- Well, to Michelangelo, it was.

15:42.408 --> 15:44.399
Michelangelo needed the...
needed the job...

15:44.476 --> 15:47.138
'cause it paid more money
than he ever had in his life.

15:47.212 --> 15:50.204
That way, he could pay off
the loan sharks that were
chasing his father down.

15:50.282 --> 15:54.446
- What's his father?
- He was, uh, like a low-level con guy.

15:54.520 --> 15:56.613
He conned people
out of money, goats, sheep.

15:56.689 --> 15:58.486
- Goats?
- Chickens, whatever he could.

15:58.557 --> 16:00.184
- Chickens?
- Chickens?
- Chickens?

16:00.259 --> 16:02.250
- You know what happened?
- What?
- What?

16:02.328 --> 16:04.319
He painted a ceiling
no one will ever forget.

16:04.396 --> 16:06.990
Painted like it was touched
by the hand of God.

16:07.066 --> 16:09.660
- Did he pay off the loans?
- Every single one.

16:09.735 --> 16:12.863
Hey, Father, how long did it take him?
You know, painting the ceiling and all?

16:12.938 --> 16:15.839
- Took him about nine years.
- Nine years?

16:15.908 --> 16:17.637
- That's right.
- That's a big ceiling.

16:17.710 --> 16:19.803
I had a Puerto Rican guy
do my whole apartment in two days.

16:19.878 --> 16:21.539
And he had a bum leg.

16:21.613 --> 16:23.843
You know, I don't know
what I'm gonna do with you guys.

16:25.184 --> 16:27.846
- Hey, just give us a job painting.
- You know what it was?
You know what it was?

16:27.920 --> 16:29.911
- The Sistine Chapel.
- Sixteenth Chapel?

16:29.989 --> 16:32.583
- Sistine Chapel.
- Who painted the other 15?

16:40.599 --> 16:42.590
Outside events meant little.

16:42.668 --> 16:45.000
In a society changing radically
by the hour...

16:45.070 --> 16:48.198
we watched the images scatter nightly
across the TV screens.

16:48.273 --> 16:50.901
Young protesters spoke about
how they were gonna change our lives...

16:50.976 --> 16:53.274
and fix the world.

16:53.345 --> 16:55.813
But while they shouted their slogans...

16:55.881 --> 16:57.872
my friends and I
went to funeral services...

16:57.950 --> 16:59.941
for the young men of Hell's Kitchen...

17:00.019 --> 17:03.045
who came back from Vietnam
in body bags.

17:03.122 --> 17:06.489
We viewed with skepticism
the faces on television...

17:06.558 --> 17:09.617
those protected by money
and upper middle-class standing.

17:12.297 --> 17:15.824
A growing army of feminists
marched across the country...

17:15.901 --> 17:17.892
demanding equality...

17:17.970 --> 17:19.961
yet our mothers still
cooked and cared for men...

17:20.039 --> 17:22.030
who abused them
mentally and physically.

17:24.209 --> 17:27.701
For me and my friends,
these developments carried no weight.

17:27.780 --> 17:30.374
They might as well have occurred
in another country...

17:30.449 --> 17:32.644
in another century.

17:32.718 --> 17:34.879
Our attention was elsewhere.

17:34.953 --> 17:38.013
We sat with Father Bobby in a third
floor hospital ward visiting John...

17:38.090 --> 17:40.388
hoping he'd recover
from a punctured lung...

17:40.459 --> 17:42.950
a gift from one of his mother's
overzealous boyfriends.

17:43.028 --> 17:45.087
I hope you like these.

17:45.164 --> 17:48.156
- You better not tell me you don't.
- Okay.

17:51.003 --> 17:53.198
Father Bobby
didn't let that situation rest.

17:53.272 --> 17:56.332
- I gave on Sunday. I'm in a rush, okay?
- John Reilly.

17:56.408 --> 17:59.900
Little punk. He got out of line,
so I put him back in line. No big deal.

17:59.978 --> 18:02.742
- You put him in the hospital.
- He's alive, ain't he?

18:02.815 --> 18:05.477
Look, if he's smart
he learned himself a lesson.

18:05.551 --> 18:08.816
- What are you, about 220? 230?
- Yeah.

18:08.887 --> 18:12.823
You're a big guy. How much
do you thinkJohn Reilly weighs?

18:12.891 --> 18:16.884
80? 85?
That's not even a featherweight.

18:16.962 --> 18:19.453
If this were a fight,
you'd be way out of your division.

18:19.531 --> 18:23.433
Look, it was a slap.
It was nothing.

18:23.502 --> 18:25.970
Well, next time you'll be meeting me.

18:26.038 --> 18:28.029
And I may not be in your division...

18:28.107 --> 18:30.667
but I do weigh more than 85 pounds.

18:30.742 --> 18:32.676
And you won't need a doctor
when I'm done.

18:32.744 --> 18:36.510
You'll need a priest
to pray over your body.

18:40.552 --> 18:42.543
See you in church.

18:47.292 --> 18:49.760
Father Bobby would have
made a good hit man.

18:49.828 --> 18:52.729
It's a shame we lost him
to the other side.

18:55.200 --> 18:58.727
We were down 7-6 in the last inning
of a sewer-to-sewer stickball game...

18:58.804 --> 19:01.967
- Against Hector Maldonado
and three of his friends.
- Come on, Mike.

19:02.040 --> 19:04.201
Come on, Davy!
Strike this chump out!

19:04.276 --> 19:06.608
- He got nothin'!
- Shut up!

19:06.678 --> 19:09.078
- Who's that?
- Sister.

19:10.082 --> 19:12.073
- What happened to her?
- I'm not sure.

19:12.151 --> 19:14.813
Some kind of cancer got in her legs
or somethin'. Worry about the game.

19:14.887 --> 19:16.878
- Come on.
- That's true. Come on. Hit a home run.

19:16.955 --> 19:18.946
Come on, Davy!
Strike this scumbag out!

19:19.024 --> 19:21.254
He can't touch you, Davy!
He can't touch you!

19:21.326 --> 19:23.988
Hey, while you don't got any legs,
you got a lot of tongue!

19:24.062 --> 19:25.893
This is it. Home run.

19:25.964 --> 19:28.489
- Oh, easy, Mike.
- Yeah, Davy!

19:28.567 --> 19:30.933
What the fuck you looking at,
little dick?

19:31.970 --> 19:33.904
- She's nothing but charm.
- Come on. All right, man.

19:33.972 --> 19:35.735
- Let's play!
- Come on, Davy!
- You take him.

19:35.807 --> 19:39.299
- You can take him, Mikey.
- Yeah! I told you he wasn't shit, baby!

19:39.378 --> 19:41.676
Hey, swallow your tongue,
you little gimp bitch!

19:41.747 --> 19:44.580
You could've helped her
across the street or you could've
bought her an ice cream.

19:44.650 --> 19:48.484
- Didn't have to throw the game.
- Yeah, now we're the Salvation Army.

19:48.554 --> 19:50.886
You ever wonder why
there ain't a Salvation Navy?

19:50.956 --> 19:54.949
Game over, losers.
Cough up the cash. A buck each.

19:55.027 --> 19:57.621
- He's no better than you.
- He was today.

19:57.696 --> 19:59.721
No, you let him be...

19:59.798 --> 20:02.858
all because Irish here has a thing
for little girls with no legs.

20:02.935 --> 20:05.301
Stay away from us, Fat Man.
All right?

20:05.370 --> 20:07.361
You boys are soft like bread.

20:07.439 --> 20:10.931
It's going to catch up to you, and
when it does, it's going to hurt bad.

20:11.009 --> 20:14.172
What happens is our business,
not yours. Okay?

20:14.246 --> 20:16.237
You gotta stay tough to be tough.

20:16.315 --> 20:19.250
Guy smells it when you're weak,
eat you like a salad.

20:19.318 --> 20:22.185
You see that street?
That street is the dish of life.

20:22.254 --> 20:24.245
And you boys are appetizers.

20:24.323 --> 20:27.656
Somebody gonna come along, eat you up
and forget about you by dessert.

20:27.726 --> 20:30.388
Take it easy, Fat Man.
It was just a stickball game.

20:30.462 --> 20:33.363
Yes, but going soft
is a habit, you know?

20:33.432 --> 20:37.027
You have to keep yourself mean
and guide your life around it.

20:37.102 --> 20:39.093
- All right, all right, calm down.
- It's the only way for boys.

20:39.171 --> 20:41.469
It's like hanging out
with fuckin' Confucius over here.

20:41.540 --> 20:43.474
- Yeah.
- Be funny, limp dick.

20:43.542 --> 20:46.534
Look, this just free advice from me to
you. You take it or you throw it away.

20:46.612 --> 20:49.479
- It don't matter.
- Thanks a lot, Fat Man.

20:51.216 --> 20:53.980
In truth, we were all surprised
by Michael's actions...

20:54.052 --> 20:56.043
but in his mind losing that game...

20:56.121 --> 20:58.612
and handing a feeling of victory
to a girl in a wheelchair...

20:58.690 --> 21:01.056
was more than the right thing to do.

21:09.935 --> 21:11.766
Come on. Let's go swimming.

21:11.837 --> 21:13.828
The temperature
topped out at 98 degrees...

21:13.905 --> 21:16.271
on the day our lives
were forever altered.

21:16.341 --> 21:19.276
I'm frying like an egg up here.
I say we get some butter rolls...

21:19.344 --> 21:21.812
a couple of sodas, and head down
to the docks to cool off.

21:21.880 --> 21:24.041
- It's hot.
- Can't you feel the breeze up here?
- What breeze?

21:24.116 --> 21:26.778
- We're surrounded by a wall, genius.
- The devil couldn't even stand this.

21:26.852 --> 21:29.821
Will you guys shut up, please?
I'm trying to get my burn.

21:29.888 --> 21:33.722
- It's 98 degrees, John.
- There's some breeze up here.
- It's a hot breeze.

21:33.792 --> 21:36.283
We haven't hit the hot dog vendor
in a couple of weeks.

21:36.361 --> 21:40.024
I don't know, Mikey.
That cart guy ain't like the others.

21:40.098 --> 21:43.625
I mean, he gets pretty pissed... like
crazy... when you try to take him off.

21:43.702 --> 21:47.798
We can eat hot dogs,
or we can eat air. Choose.

21:49.374 --> 21:51.137
Air's probably safer, Mike.

21:51.209 --> 21:53.575
Yeah, a hot dog ain't worth
bleedin' over, Mikey.

21:53.645 --> 21:57.137
- Yeah, but anyway, whose turn was it?
- Yours.

21:57.215 --> 21:59.843
- Yeah, it's yours.
- Mine? It's not my turn.

21:59.918 --> 22:01.909
- Yes, it is.
- I went, like, last month.

22:01.987 --> 22:03.978
- He went two weeks...
- You never went.
- Last month.

22:04.056 --> 22:06.786
- Are you nuts? I went right after him.
- I'm not going.
- Why?

22:06.858 --> 22:09.554
- It's too hot.
- Why not?
- I walk down the stairs, I'll pass out.

22:13.332 --> 22:15.493
Mustard, onions, no soda.

22:15.567 --> 22:19.333
- I know you.
- I look like a lot of people.

22:19.404 --> 22:21.065
The scam was simple.

22:21.139 --> 22:24.404
I was to walk up to the hot dog vendor
and order what I wanted.

22:24.476 --> 22:28.435
The vendor would then hand me my hot dog
and watch as I ran off without paying.

22:28.513 --> 22:31.573
This left the vendor with two choices,
neither very appealing.

22:31.650 --> 22:35.177
He could stand his ground and swallow
his loss, or he could give chase.

22:35.253 --> 22:37.414
The second forces him
to abandon the cart...

22:37.489 --> 22:40.083
where my friends could feast
in his absence.

22:42.361 --> 22:44.352
Uh, I'm gonna need two napkins.

22:46.131 --> 22:48.122
Hey, my money! Thief!

22:49.134 --> 22:51.068
<i>Well, my temperature's rising</i>

22:51.136 --> 22:53.127
- <i>And my feet on the floor</i>
- Yes!

22:53.205 --> 22:56.140
- <i>Twenty people knockin'</i>
<i>'cause they're wanting some more</i>
- All aboard. Ketchup.

22:56.208 --> 22:57.903
I took it from him and ran.

22:57.976 --> 23:02.310
I scooted past Tommy Mung's Dry Cleaners
and Armand's Shoe Repair.

23:02.381 --> 23:06.613
The vendor gave chase, a wooden-handled,
pronged fork in one hand.

23:06.685 --> 23:09.119
All right. More. Give me two.

23:10.122 --> 23:13.455
- <i>Gimme some</i>
- <i>Gimme, gimme some lovin'</i>

23:13.525 --> 23:16.688
- <i>Gimme some lovin'</i>
- <i>Gimme, gimme some lovin'</i>

23:16.762 --> 23:19.287
<i>Gimme some lovin'every day</i>

23:19.364 --> 23:21.594
You know, these things
are heavier than they look.

23:21.666 --> 23:24.760
Genius, these are gas tanks
to keep the food hot.

23:24.836 --> 23:26.997
They're heavier than shit.

23:27.072 --> 23:29.563
Think we can push it,
the three of us?

23:29.641 --> 23:32.439
- Push it where, huh?
- Couple of blocks.

23:32.511 --> 23:35.571
Be a nice surprise for the guy, when
he comes back from chasing Shakes...

23:35.647 --> 23:37.808
not to find his cart.

23:37.883 --> 23:39.714
<i>Hey</i>

23:41.319 --> 23:44.618
<i>Well, I feel so good</i>
<i>Everything is sounding hot</i>

23:44.689 --> 23:48.352
<i>You better take it easy</i>
<i>'cause the place is on fire</i>

23:48.427 --> 23:51.362
<i>Been a hard day</i>
<i>and I have so much to do</i>

23:51.430 --> 23:54.263
<i>We made it, baby</i>
<i>and it happened to you</i>

23:54.332 --> 23:57.768
<i>And I'm so glad we made it</i>

23:57.836 --> 24:02.000
The vendor tired at 47 th and 9th.
I was on the other side of the street.

24:04.042 --> 24:06.704
He was beat, but not beaten.

24:06.778 --> 24:09.713
He could go 10 minutes more
just on hate alone.

24:09.781 --> 24:13.046
Come on. Give it up.

24:26.097 --> 24:28.156
What's wrong, Mikey?

24:28.233 --> 24:31.760
Shakes is taking too long.
He should've been back by now.

24:31.837 --> 24:33.828
He'll be fine. He's Shakes.

24:33.905 --> 24:36.396
<i>You better take it easy</i>
<i>'cause the place is on fire</i>

24:36.475 --> 24:38.966
You guys were supposed to take
the hot dogs, not the wagon.

24:39.044 --> 24:41.205
- Oh, now he tells us.
- He's coming fast, Mikey.

24:41.279 --> 24:43.270
- He's still running?
- He's coming?

24:43.348 --> 24:46.010
I got a plan.
Come on. Over by the subway.

24:46.084 --> 24:48.075
The plan, as it turned out,
was as simple...

24:48.153 --> 24:50.178
and as dumb as anything
we'd ever done.

24:50.255 --> 24:52.689
We were to hold the cart
on the top edge of the stairwell...

24:52.757 --> 24:54.918
leaning it downward,
and wait for the vendor.

24:54.993 --> 24:56.984
We were to let it go
the second he grabbed the handles.

24:57.062 --> 24:59.053
Then we'd leave the scene
as he struggled...

24:59.130 --> 25:01.121
to ease the cart
back onto the sidewalk.

25:01.199 --> 25:03.565
To this day,
I don't know why we did it...

25:03.635 --> 25:06.069
but we would all pay a price.

25:06.137 --> 25:09.470
It only took a minute,
but in that minute everything changed.

25:09.541 --> 25:11.202
- You got it?
- Shit. Hold it up.

25:11.276 --> 25:14.734
I can't hold it! I can't hold it!
I can't hold it!

25:14.813 --> 25:17.213
- Hold it up! Come on!
- I can't!

25:17.282 --> 25:19.375
- Shit!
- No!

25:30.428 --> 25:32.896
Stop! Get out of... No!

25:55.520 --> 25:57.249
Damn!

26:01.560 --> 26:03.892
- My God!
- SweetJesus!

26:03.962 --> 26:06.089
What have you boys done?

26:06.164 --> 26:08.724
What in the name of God
have you boys done?

26:08.800 --> 26:10.791
I think we just killed a man.

26:15.740 --> 26:19.369
WhileJames Caldwell was slowly
recovering at St. Claire's Hospital...

26:19.444 --> 26:21.435
we were charged
with reckless endangerment...

26:21.513 --> 26:23.504
and remanded
into our parents' custody.

26:24.349 --> 26:28.308
- I'm sorry, Dad!
- That ain't gonna do you much good.

26:28.386 --> 26:31.685
Take it easy!
This is no time to get crazy!

26:32.357 --> 26:35.190
You're going to jail, and you don't
even know what the fuck that means!

26:35.260 --> 26:37.091
Ma!

26:38.096 --> 26:40.530
You stay out of this.
He's just a kid.

26:40.599 --> 26:44.035
He shouldn't have to do time. Nobody
in this family should have to do time.

26:44.102 --> 26:47.503
I done enough time for everybody!

27:12.697 --> 27:14.688
I hear you're short an altar boy.

27:18.403 --> 27:20.394
You still remember what to do?

27:21.406 --> 27:24.739
Easy on the water,
heavy on the wine...

27:24.809 --> 27:28.176
and ring the bells whenever
I see someone start to nod off.

27:28.246 --> 27:30.908
Get ready. We got five minutes
till showtime.

27:43.495 --> 27:45.486
I'm gonna miss this.

27:47.932 --> 27:49.923
I'm gonna miss all this.

27:51.336 --> 27:55.067
I've been doing all I can,
but so far every door I touch is locked.

27:59.511 --> 28:01.945
I could run.

28:02.013 --> 28:04.004
We all could run.

28:06.051 --> 28:08.076
Disappear for a while.

28:08.153 --> 28:10.212
Nobody's gonna come looking.

28:11.556 --> 28:13.547
Nobody's gonna care about us...

28:14.826 --> 28:16.987
about where we go.

28:21.499 --> 28:24.593
You run now,
you're gonna run till you die.

28:26.371 --> 28:28.703
Hiding's not gonna make it go away.

28:28.773 --> 28:30.866
People aren't gonna forget.

28:32.110 --> 28:34.101
You've gotta face this.

28:39.751 --> 28:41.742
I can't, Father.

28:43.688 --> 28:45.679
I don't wanna face it.

28:47.459 --> 28:49.450
I'm too scared to face it.

28:51.062 --> 28:53.053
I'm scared too.

28:53.131 --> 28:56.100
Nobody's more scared than I am.

28:56.167 --> 28:58.658
But you gotta do it.

29:00.505 --> 29:02.837
You're gonna be okay.

29:02.907 --> 29:05.535
You're gonna make it through there.

29:05.610 --> 29:07.601
You understand?

29:12.217 --> 29:14.947
Come on. We got an audience.

29:21.259 --> 29:24.922
I counted three rummies
and four widows on my way in.

29:26.998 --> 29:30.434
Plus, Fat Ralphie's sleeping one off
in the last row.

29:31.436 --> 29:34.098
It's the rain. Bad weather
always brings in the crowds.

29:40.245 --> 29:42.805
This is one of my favorites.

29:42.881 --> 29:44.542
What is?

29:45.683 --> 29:50.279
"Whatever you do to the least
of my brethren, you do to me."

29:54.425 --> 29:56.086
Come on.

30:02.267 --> 30:04.428
We never saw the vendor as a man...

30:04.502 --> 30:07.369
not the way we saw
other men of the neighborhood...

30:07.438 --> 30:10.965
and we didn't care enough about him
to grant him any respect.

30:11.042 --> 30:13.533
We gave little notice
to how hard he worked...

30:13.611 --> 30:16.239
or that he had a wife
and two kids in Greece...

30:16.314 --> 30:18.305
and hoped to bring them
to this country.

30:18.383 --> 30:20.749
We didn't pay attention
to the long hours he worked.

30:20.819 --> 30:22.810
We didn't see any of that.

30:22.887 --> 30:25.321
We only saw a free lunch.

30:27.392 --> 30:30.020
Thomas Marcano, the Court
hereby sentences you...

30:30.094 --> 30:33.996
to be remanded for a period of no more
than 18 months, no less than one year...

30:34.065 --> 30:35.999
at the Wilkinson Home for Boys.

30:36.067 --> 30:38.831
John Reilly, the Court
hereby sentences you...

30:38.903 --> 30:43.033
to be remanded for a period of no more
than 18 months, no less than one year...

30:43.107 --> 30:45.041
to the Wilkinson Home for Boys.

30:45.109 --> 30:47.100
Lorenzo Carcaterra...

30:48.112 --> 30:51.081
taking into consideration
that you arrived on the scene...

30:51.149 --> 30:53.583
after the theft of the cart
had already occurred...

30:53.651 --> 30:56.347
in consideration of that, the Court
hereby sentences you to serve...

30:56.421 --> 30:58.821
no more than one year,
no less than six months...

30:58.890 --> 31:00.881
at the Wilkinson Home for Boys.

31:02.227 --> 31:04.058
Michael Sullivan...

31:04.128 --> 31:06.460
the Court hereby sentences you
to be remanded for a period...

31:06.531 --> 31:10.729
of no more than 18 months, no less than
one year at the Wilkinson Home for Boys.

31:10.802 --> 31:14.135
And I might add, had it not been for the
intervention of Father Robert Carillo...

31:14.205 --> 31:17.003
who spoke in glowing terms
on your behalf...

31:17.075 --> 31:20.272
I would have sentenced you
to a much stiffer punishment.

31:20.345 --> 31:22.643
I still have my doubts
as to your inherent goodness...

31:22.714 --> 31:25.148
but only time will serve
to prove me wrong.

31:28.686 --> 31:31.917
- Could you do me a favor, Father?
- What do you want? Name it.

31:31.990 --> 31:33.981
The past couple of weeks...

31:34.058 --> 31:37.221
my mother and father looked like
they were ready to kill each other.

31:37.295 --> 31:39.889
- Could you watch over 'em for me?
- I will.

31:40.899 --> 31:45.063
And no matter what you hear,
tell 'em I'm doing okay.

31:45.136 --> 31:48.003
You mean, you want me to lie?

31:48.072 --> 31:51.064
It's a good lie, Father.
You can do it.

31:53.711 --> 31:55.906
Come on. Let's go.

31:56.981 --> 31:59.848
- Be strong.
- I will.

32:36.788 --> 32:40.519
The Wilkinson Home for Boys
held 780 youthful offenders...

32:40.591 --> 32:42.718
housed in five separate units.

32:42.794 --> 32:44.955
From the outside,
the facility resembled...

32:45.029 --> 32:47.964
what those who ran it
wanted it to resemble...

32:48.032 --> 32:50.694
some kind of nice school
or university.

32:52.036 --> 32:56.302
Michael, Tommy, John and I were
assigned to the second floor of group C.

32:56.374 --> 32:58.865
We each had a private 12-foot room.

32:58.943 --> 33:03.437
I'd been in my room less than an hour
when the panic set in.

33:03.514 --> 33:06.312
It doesn't take very long to know
how tough a person you are...

33:06.384 --> 33:08.375
or how strong you can be.

33:08.453 --> 33:12.890
I knew from my first day at Wilkinson
that I was neither tough nor strong.

33:24.068 --> 33:26.002
Hello, Carcaterra.

33:27.572 --> 33:31.440
- Toss your clothes on the floor.
- Here?

33:31.509 --> 33:33.670
What, are you expecting a dressing room?
We don't have any.

33:33.745 --> 33:36.270
- Now, lose the clothes.
- In front of you?

33:44.689 --> 33:46.953
Let's go. Let's go.

33:56.834 --> 34:00.099
What's that piece of shit
around your neck? Take it off.

34:00.171 --> 34:02.298
It's Mary.
You know, the Mother of God.

34:02.373 --> 34:05.467
I don't give a fuck whose mother it is.
Take it off.

34:18.089 --> 34:20.080
Everything.

34:20.158 --> 34:23.719
- So you want me to stand here naked?
- Now you're catching on.

34:23.795 --> 34:27.253
I knew you Hell's Kitchen boys
weren't as dumb as everyone says.

34:34.505 --> 34:36.803
Now what?

34:38.376 --> 34:40.367
Get dressed.

34:44.549 --> 34:46.540
There were four guards
assigned to each floor...

34:46.617 --> 34:51.077
with one... in our case, Nokes...
designated group leader.

34:52.123 --> 34:54.614
Ferguson was the only son
of a slain New York state trooper...

34:54.692 --> 34:56.683
and was on the waiting list
for both the New York City...

34:56.761 --> 34:58.922
and Suffolk County
police departments.

34:58.996 --> 35:03.456
Styler was using his job at Wilkinson's
to finance his way through law school.

35:03.534 --> 35:05.525
Addison was a graduate
of the local high school...

35:05.603 --> 35:08.436
who wanted nothing more
than a steady job that paid well.

35:08.506 --> 35:09.996
Hey. Come on. Quit pushing.

35:10.074 --> 35:12.736
It was not a group
of innocent young boys at Wilkinson.

35:12.810 --> 35:14.971
Most, if not all, the inmates
belonged there.

35:15.046 --> 35:17.981
A number of them were riding out
their second and third convictions.

35:18.049 --> 35:22.213
All were violent offenders. Few seemed
sorry about what they had done.

35:22.286 --> 35:24.413
And as for rehabilitation?

35:24.489 --> 35:26.320
Forget it.

35:31.729 --> 35:33.390
Mikey.

35:34.632 --> 35:36.122
Yeah, all right.

36:01.559 --> 36:04.494
Hey, what the fuck
did you do that for?

36:04.562 --> 36:07.963
- You got close to me.
- So?

36:08.032 --> 36:10.330
It bothers me.

36:10.401 --> 36:13.666
I don't wanna be near you
or your creeped-out friends.

36:18.309 --> 36:20.368
Whoa! Yes!

36:20.444 --> 36:22.378
Fight!

37:09.527 --> 37:12.826
You know, your time here
hasn't taught you shit.

37:13.831 --> 37:16.163
You're still the same
fuckin' bunch of clowns you were...

37:16.234 --> 37:18.327
the day you walked in here.

37:19.704 --> 37:23.800
Okay. Everybody go on back
and finish your lunches.

37:23.874 --> 37:25.865
There's nothing more to see.

37:27.044 --> 37:29.444
Go on, go. Sit down.
Get out of here.

37:31.816 --> 37:34.512
Go on.

37:34.585 --> 37:36.576
Go ahead.

37:43.327 --> 37:46.819
- That go for me too?
- No, it don't go for you.

37:46.897 --> 37:49.730
You go back to your room.
You're through with your lunch.

37:50.768 --> 37:52.861
Go on.

37:52.937 --> 37:56.134
You and me, we're gonna finish this
sometime real soon.

37:56.207 --> 38:00.109
- Yeah, maybe at dinner.
- So...

38:00.177 --> 38:02.611
you Hell's Kitchen boys
get any lunch?

38:04.815 --> 38:07.409
I got to smell it.

38:07.485 --> 38:09.476
You got to smell it.

38:12.957 --> 38:14.720
That's good.
Hey, hey, hey!

38:14.792 --> 38:17.022
Where you goin'?

38:17.094 --> 38:19.028
You said to get lunch.

38:19.096 --> 38:22.031
Oh, you boys don't need to get back
in line to get lunch, 'cause...

38:22.099 --> 38:25.557
there's plenty to eat
right where you're standing.

38:25.636 --> 38:27.627
You can smell it.

38:32.576 --> 38:34.737
I'm not hungry.

38:34.812 --> 38:37.747
Well, I don't give a fuck
if you're hungry or not.

38:37.815 --> 38:40.477
You eat because
I'm telling you to eat.

38:44.822 --> 38:46.653
I'm still not hungry.

38:52.296 --> 38:55.925
I'll tell you when you're
hungry or not. Now eat.

38:58.402 --> 39:01.166
Excuse me.
What the fuck are you looking at?

39:01.238 --> 39:06.005
Get the fuck down on your knees now
and finish your goddamn lunch!

39:07.011 --> 39:10.811
Come on. Now, eat! Don't think
you got all fucking day here! Eat!

39:10.881 --> 39:14.544
You got some mashed potatoes.
Come on. Suck up some of thatJell-O.

39:14.618 --> 39:16.916
Come on, now,
you fuckin' assholes. Eat.

39:16.987 --> 39:19.956
Don't be thinking you got all day.
Hurry up. Come on. Now, let's go.

39:20.024 --> 39:22.356
Let's go. Hey!

39:22.426 --> 39:23.859
None of you clowns are leaving here...

39:23.928 --> 39:26.294
until these assholes finish
their goddamn lunch.

39:26.364 --> 39:28.093
You got that?

39:28.165 --> 39:30.156
Hey, you. Here's a piece of bread.
There you go.

39:30.234 --> 39:33.260
You can't have a good lunch
without a nice piece of bread. Eat!

39:33.337 --> 39:36.135
Let's go! Come on, now.
That's good.

39:36.207 --> 39:38.903
That's good. Yeah, show the boys
how you follow my rules.

39:38.976 --> 39:42.434
Rules! You understand?

39:42.513 --> 39:45.949
Hey, look, boys.
See how he follows my rules?

39:46.016 --> 39:48.075
Shift's over, Nokes.

39:48.152 --> 39:50.313
No, l-l... I'm not ready to go yet.

39:50.388 --> 39:54.188
I still got a few more things I gotta
clean up here before I can leave.

39:54.258 --> 39:57.193
This is my tour now.
I'll clean what needs cleaning.

39:57.261 --> 40:00.230
Stay out of this one.
It's got nothing to do with you.

40:00.297 --> 40:03.562
This one I'm staying in.

40:06.971 --> 40:09.405
Don't fuck with me, boy.

40:10.408 --> 40:12.399
No, Nokes...

40:12.476 --> 40:15.172
you fuck with me.

40:15.246 --> 40:17.908
I'm asking you.

40:23.521 --> 40:25.580
You're eatin' into my shift.

40:28.159 --> 40:31.993
I'll get out of your way for now.

40:32.997 --> 40:35.192
I'll take what I can get.

40:37.067 --> 40:39.797
You boys get off your knees.

40:52.349 --> 40:55.944
It's a tragedy.
I'll tell you...

40:56.020 --> 40:58.284
I don't understand you boys.

40:58.355 --> 41:00.516
I don't think you know
what it means to have rules.

41:00.591 --> 41:03.617
You gotta have rules
and you gotta have discipline.

41:03.694 --> 41:06.527
Now, I don't know what it was like
in your homes and your home lives...

41:06.597 --> 41:10.533
but in my house, with my father,
there were rules...

41:10.601 --> 41:14.401
and if you... you didn't follow
the rules, there was hell to pay.

41:14.472 --> 41:17.464
You had rules,
and you had discipline.

41:18.542 --> 41:22.000
Sometimes it wasn't nice,
but, boy, we learned.

41:22.079 --> 41:23.740
We sure did learn.

41:25.483 --> 41:28.816
Yeah, right around there to the right.
There you go. Come on, now.

41:34.425 --> 41:36.518
I mean, it's a simple thing, really.

41:36.594 --> 41:39.825
You got rules,
and you got discipline.

41:39.897 --> 41:42.923
That's the beginning of the story,
and that's the end of the story.

41:49.974 --> 41:52.568
- Do we understand each other?
- Turn and face the wall.

41:52.643 --> 41:54.634
Face the wall.

41:58.182 --> 42:00.343
You too.

42:02.319 --> 42:05.755
Now, we got interrupted earlier
in the lunch room...

42:05.823 --> 42:09.122
but there's no one
to interrupt us here now.

42:19.236 --> 42:21.067
What do you want?

42:22.973 --> 42:25.703
A blow job.

42:25.776 --> 42:27.767
Face the wall!

42:32.249 --> 42:34.740
Down on your knees.

42:37.054 --> 42:39.045
Face the wall. Face it!

42:56.173 --> 42:59.438
There are no clear pictures
of the sexual abuse we endured.

42:59.510 --> 43:02.775
I buried it as deep
as it can possibly go.

43:02.846 --> 43:05.508
What I remember most clearly
from that chilly October night...

43:05.583 --> 43:07.983
was that it was my 14th birthday...

43:08.052 --> 43:10.043
and the end of my childhood.

43:19.897 --> 43:23.526
Early in my stay, I'd written
and asked my father not to come.

43:23.601 --> 43:25.592
I couldn't look at my father
and have him see in my face...

43:25.669 --> 43:27.534
all that had happened to me.

43:27.605 --> 43:30.699
Michael had done the same with
the interested members of his family.

43:30.774 --> 43:33.208
Tommy's mother couldn't
get it together to visit.

43:33.277 --> 43:35.438
John's mother
came up once a month.

43:38.649 --> 43:41.948
But no one could stop
Father Bobby from visiting.

43:43.287 --> 43:47.053
So listen, let's try to keep this
on a happy note, okay?

43:47.124 --> 43:50.059
Nokes warned us not to say anything
to Father Bobby.

43:50.127 --> 43:53.324
If we did,
the reprisals would be severe.

44:07.645 --> 44:09.977
You lost a few pounds.

44:10.047 --> 44:12.880
It's not exactly home cookin'.

44:12.950 --> 44:15.248
Sit down.

44:15.319 --> 44:18.755
So, I get to see
all four of you guys today.

44:18.822 --> 44:22.656
I loved Father Bobby,
but I couldn't stand to look at him.

44:22.726 --> 44:25.559
I was afraid he'd look right through me,
past the fear and the shame...

44:25.629 --> 44:27.062
right through to the truth.

44:27.131 --> 44:30.498
Shakes, is there anything
you wanna tell me?

44:31.502 --> 44:33.527
Anything at all?

44:34.538 --> 44:37.234
You shouldn't come here
anymore, Father.

44:39.076 --> 44:41.067
I appreciate it and all.

44:42.079 --> 44:44.411
I don't think it's
the right thing for you to do.

45:08.706 --> 45:13.109
I stopped off at Attica today on my way
up here to see an old friend of mine.

45:13.177 --> 45:15.270
You have any friends not in jail?

45:16.880 --> 45:18.871
Not as many as I would like.

45:20.084 --> 45:22.552
What's he in for?

45:22.619 --> 45:24.450
Triple murder.

45:24.521 --> 45:26.989
He killed three men
about 15 years ago.

45:28.225 --> 45:31.558
- And he's a good friend?
- Yeah, he was my best friend.

45:33.864 --> 45:35.695
We hung out together.

45:35.766 --> 45:38.496
We were close,
just like you and the guys.

45:50.514 --> 45:53.244
We were both sent up here.

45:55.552 --> 45:57.543
That's right.

45:59.123 --> 46:01.114
And it wasn't easy.

46:02.126 --> 46:05.118
Just like it's not easy
for you and the guys.

46:06.897 --> 46:09.024
This place killed him.

46:09.099 --> 46:11.431
Made him not care anymore.

46:15.472 --> 46:17.633
Don't let this place
do that to you, Shakes.

46:18.642 --> 46:22.544
Don't let it make you think
you're tougher than you are.

46:22.613 --> 46:24.604
I gotta go, Father.

46:32.422 --> 46:34.913
I'll see you in the Kitchen, hmm?

46:36.093 --> 46:38.084
I'm counting on you now.

46:39.096 --> 46:42.554
Wipe the tears off your face.
Don't let them see it.

46:42.633 --> 46:44.692
Don't let 'em see you crying.

46:44.768 --> 46:47.259
Don't give them the satisfaction.

46:49.740 --> 46:51.731
You'll be out of here
before you know it.

46:55.312 --> 46:57.712
You're gonna be okay.

47:03.453 --> 47:05.614
I didn't want to let him go.

47:05.689 --> 47:08.954
I never felt as close to anyone
as I felt to him that moment.

47:15.766 --> 47:18.257
A number of the inmates,
as tough as they acted during the day...

47:18.335 --> 47:21.532
would often cry themselves
to sleep at night.

47:21.605 --> 47:23.596
There were other cries too.

47:23.674 --> 47:26.905
These differed from those
filled with fear and loneliness.

47:26.977 --> 47:28.968
They were low and muffled...

47:29.046 --> 47:31.708
the sounds of pained anguish.

47:31.782 --> 47:34.774
Those cries can change
the course of a life.

47:34.852 --> 47:38.379
They are cries that, once heard,
can never be erased from memory.

47:38.455 --> 47:41.618
On this one night, those cries
belonged to my friend John...

47:41.692 --> 47:44.183
when Ralph Ferguson paid him a visit.

48:00.510 --> 48:03.604
I was expecting to read
30 book reports over the weekend.

48:03.680 --> 48:05.807
There were only six for me to read.

48:05.883 --> 48:07.874
Which means I'm missing how many?

48:08.886 --> 48:12.788
Man, this is English class.
Math's down the hall.

48:16.059 --> 48:19.119
Now, I want to help you.
You may not believe that...

48:19.196 --> 48:22.097
or you may not care,
but it's the truth.

48:28.972 --> 48:31.964
- You got a second?
- What, I do something wrong?

48:32.042 --> 48:35.239
No. You did a great job
on your book report.

48:36.880 --> 48:39.974
You really seemed to like the book.
<i>The Count of Monte Cristo. </i>

48:40.050 --> 48:43.451
It's my favorite. I liked it more
since that I've been in here.

48:43.520 --> 48:45.317
Why is that?

48:46.323 --> 48:50.692
It's like he wouldn't
let anyone beat him... the count.

48:50.761 --> 48:52.592
Took what he had to take...

48:52.663 --> 48:55.393
the beatings, insults and whatever...

48:55.465 --> 48:57.763
and he learned from it.

48:57.834 --> 49:02.498
Then when the time came for him
to do something, he made his move.

49:02.572 --> 49:05.769
- You admire that?
- No, I respect that.

49:07.277 --> 49:09.802
You... You got a copy
of the book at home?

49:09.880 --> 49:12.644
I got the <i>Classics Illustrated</i> comic.

49:12.716 --> 49:14.707
No, it's not the same thing.

49:14.785 --> 49:17.049
Listen, I gotta go.
I'm gonna miss morning roll call.

49:17.120 --> 49:20.647
Wait, wait, wait. One minute, one
minute. I've got something for you.

49:21.858 --> 49:25.191
- Thought you might like to have it.
- Are you serious?

49:25.262 --> 49:28.754
Well, you loved the book that much,
you should have a copy of your own.

49:28.832 --> 49:32.268
- I can't pay you.
- No, it's a gift.

49:32.336 --> 49:35.828
- You've gotten gifts before,
haven't you?
- It's been a while.

49:35.906 --> 49:38.397
Well, it's my way of saying thanks.

49:38.475 --> 49:40.443
For what?

49:40.510 --> 49:43.809
That somebody listens,
even if it's just one student.

49:43.880 --> 49:45.711
- You're a good teacher, Mr. Carlson...
- Listen...

49:45.782 --> 49:47.943
we can discuss the book
on Friday in class, if you, uh...

49:48.018 --> 49:49.883
think the count
can hold their attention.

49:49.953 --> 49:51.944
He's got a shot.

49:52.022 --> 49:54.115
Any particular section
I should read from?

49:54.191 --> 49:57.285
That's easy. The part
where he escapes from prison.

50:10.407 --> 50:13.865
Here you go, little star.
Here's your locker room.

50:20.684 --> 50:22.618
It was only a game...

50:22.686 --> 50:25.951
just a touch football game,
nothing more...

50:26.023 --> 50:28.355
but a game I wish
we had never played.

50:28.425 --> 50:30.723
- Hut, hut.
- Guards against inmates.

50:30.794 --> 50:33.319
The guards practiced
four times a week.

50:33.397 --> 50:36.195
- Our team was picked
the Monday before the game.
- Let's go.

50:36.266 --> 50:38.826
- We had a two-hour practice.
- Set. Hut.

50:38.902 --> 50:40.130
- Didn't matter much.
- Get him!

50:40.203 --> 50:41.898
We weren't supposed to win.

50:41.972 --> 50:43.997
We were just supposed to show up.

50:44.074 --> 50:46.542
Who's the toughest guy out here?

50:46.610 --> 50:48.441
How do you mean "tough"?

50:48.512 --> 50:50.980
- Who can talk and have everyone listen?
- Rizzo.

50:51.048 --> 50:53.039
Black kid over there.

50:54.051 --> 50:55.882
Michael saw an opening...

50:55.952 --> 50:58.944
a chance to bring the game to our level,
even out the field.

50:59.022 --> 51:02.287
But he needed help.
He needed Rizzo.

51:02.359 --> 51:04.452
Black kid with an Italian name.

51:04.528 --> 51:07.793
With Rizzo on our side,
we had a chance.

51:07.864 --> 51:11.322
Look, white boy, I don't know what
you play on the streets. I don't care.

51:11.401 --> 51:14.393
But in here the guards call the play,
and the play calls them to win the game.

51:14.471 --> 51:17.304
- Why?
- Look, man.

51:17.374 --> 51:20.707
Guards steer clear of me, all right?
They stay back and let me do my time.

51:20.777 --> 51:22.768
If I play in a game
and I put a hurtin' on one of them...

51:22.846 --> 51:24.677
that might change my cushion.

51:24.748 --> 51:28.206
I'm not saying we gotta win.
I just don't wanna take a beating.

51:28.285 --> 51:31.686
We do every day.
Why's Saturday special?

51:31.755 --> 51:33.780
'Cause on Saturday
we can hit back.

51:34.991 --> 51:36.583
Really.

51:36.660 --> 51:39.788
They don't fuck with you like they do
us, but they fuck with you another way.

51:39.863 --> 51:42.093
You're just an animal to 'em.

51:42.165 --> 51:44.861
- I don't give a fuck.
- Yeah, you do.

51:44.935 --> 51:48.564
And beating them on Saturday
is not gonna change a thing.

51:48.638 --> 51:52.802
- Then why, white boy? Why?
- To make them feel what we feel...

51:52.876 --> 51:54.867
just for a couple of hours.

51:56.413 --> 51:58.438
Now, don't try anything funny, Sambo.

51:58.515 --> 52:01.006
Nobody'll get hurt.
You know what I'm saying?

52:01.084 --> 52:03.552
- I call heads.
- He calls heads.

52:05.188 --> 52:07.349
He called heads.
It is a head.

52:09.192 --> 52:11.023
- Let's go.
- Go.

52:20.270 --> 52:24.036
You're gonna die, motherfucker.
You're gonna fucking die.

52:27.377 --> 52:29.368
- You all right?
- Yeah.

52:34.284 --> 52:36.582
None of you motherfuckers
can cover me!

52:36.653 --> 52:40.316
We got ourselves a game.
I'm feeling good today.

52:40.390 --> 52:42.255
This shit feels good.

52:47.097 --> 52:49.895
Hut, hut!

52:54.771 --> 52:57.433
- Fuck!
- Get the fuck off me!

53:04.648 --> 53:06.479
Yeah!

53:09.986 --> 53:12.318
Yeah, keep smiling,
you little pissant.

53:12.389 --> 53:13.879
Yeah.

53:15.125 --> 53:18.458
For 90 minutes,
we took the game out of the prison...

53:18.528 --> 53:20.962
moved it miles beyond the locked gates
and the sloping hills...

53:21.031 --> 53:22.965
of the surrounding countryside...

53:23.033 --> 53:27.129
and brought it back down to the streets
of the neighborhoods we'd come from.

53:27.204 --> 53:30.867
- For those 90 minutes,
we were once again free.
- Set.

53:39.349 --> 53:41.442
Yeah!

53:46.389 --> 53:49.051
Rizzo! Rizzo! Rizzo!

53:49.125 --> 53:51.821
Rizzo! Rizzo! Rizzo!

53:51.895 --> 53:54.056
Rizzo! Rizzo! Rizzo!

53:54.130 --> 53:55.563
Rizzo! Rizzo!

53:55.632 --> 53:58.100
Rizzo! Rizzo! Rizzo!

53:58.168 --> 54:00.329
Rizzo! Rizzo!

54:00.403 --> 54:02.394
- Rizzo! Rizzo! Rizzo!
- Rizzo.

54:02.472 --> 54:04.906
Rizzo.

54:04.975 --> 54:07.000
Rizzo.

54:07.077 --> 54:10.638
- Rizzo! Rizzo! Rizzo!
- Rizzo.
- Hey, Nokes.

54:10.714 --> 54:12.705
- Good game.
- Rizzo!

54:14.184 --> 54:16.175
For once, we had a victory.

54:16.253 --> 54:20.189
But it didn't last.
It couldn't last.

54:20.257 --> 54:23.420
And all I wanted to do was die.

54:23.493 --> 54:25.427
I was not alone in the hole.

54:25.495 --> 54:28.089
I knew my friends were
down in the depths with me...

54:28.164 --> 54:30.826
each in his own cell
and each in his own pain...

54:30.900 --> 54:32.834
suffering his own demons.

54:32.902 --> 54:35.496
Rizzo was there too.

54:37.173 --> 54:39.505
I had lost any sense of time.

55:19.582 --> 55:21.846
I thought you'd never wake up.

55:21.918 --> 55:23.909
I thought I'd never want to.

55:23.987 --> 55:27.218
John and Tommy
are on the other side there.

55:28.491 --> 55:31.187
How are they?

55:31.261 --> 55:33.627
They're alive.

55:33.697 --> 55:35.358
Who isn't?

55:37.033 --> 55:38.864
Rizzo.

55:40.737 --> 55:43.729
They killed him?

55:43.807 --> 55:45.900
They took turns beating him...

55:45.975 --> 55:48.944
until there was
nothing of that kid to beat.

55:52.949 --> 55:55.611
Rizzo was dead because of us.

55:55.685 --> 55:57.619
We made him think that
going up against the guards...

55:57.687 --> 56:01.179
in a meaningless football game
had some value...

56:01.257 --> 56:03.953
that it would give us
a reason to go on.

56:04.027 --> 56:07.019
Once again, we were wrong.

56:08.765 --> 56:12.531
- They give you your release date yet?
- Nokes had the letter from the warden.

56:12.602 --> 56:15.662
Waved it in front of me
then tore it up.

56:15.739 --> 56:17.639
When do you figure?

56:17.707 --> 56:21.507
I don't know. End of spring,
early summer or something.

56:21.578 --> 56:24.046
I wish we were comin' with ya.

56:24.114 --> 56:27.845
Would've been nice for all of us
to walk out together, you know.

56:27.917 --> 56:32.115
No use thinking about that. We're gonna
do a full year, and not an hour less.

56:33.556 --> 56:36.923
When I get out, I could get Father Bobby
to make a couple of phone calls, huh?

56:36.993 --> 56:39.655
- Shave a month or two off.
- There's nothin' to talk about.

56:39.729 --> 56:41.720
There's a lot to talk about.

56:41.798 --> 56:45.131
Maybe if people knew what was
going on in here they'd make a move.

56:45.201 --> 56:47.431
I don't want anybody to know.

56:47.504 --> 56:51.270
Not Father Bobby, King Benny,
Fat Mancho...

56:51.341 --> 56:54.003
not my mother, nobody.

56:55.345 --> 56:57.176
Yeah, I don't either. I mean...

56:57.247 --> 56:59.909
I wouldn't know what to say
to anyone who did know.

56:59.983 --> 57:03.077
I can't think of anybody
who needs to hear about it.

57:03.153 --> 57:05.178
I mean, either
they won't believe it...

57:05.255 --> 57:07.280
or they won't give a shit.

57:07.357 --> 57:10.884
Yeah, I don't even think we should
talk about it once it's over, you know?

57:11.928 --> 57:14.123
We got no choice
but to live with it...

57:14.197 --> 57:17.189
and talking makes living it harder...

57:17.267 --> 57:20.202
so we might as well
not even talk about it.

57:20.270 --> 57:22.261
The truth stays with us.

57:25.041 --> 57:28.238
I wanna be able
to sleep one night...

57:28.311 --> 57:30.779
and not have to worry
who's coming in my room...

57:30.847 --> 57:33.042
what's gonna happen to me.

57:35.652 --> 57:38.485
If I can get that...

57:38.555 --> 57:41.046
then I'll be happy.

57:42.492 --> 57:45.484
Someday, John. Promise.

