01:17:08.523 --> 01:17:09.854
What if I do lose?

01:17:09.925 --> 01:17:12.655
Then you go down
for the dirt nap.

01:17:12.728 --> 01:17:15.697
Never heard that expression before.

01:17:17.332 --> 01:17:20.358
Dirt nap.

01:17:20.435 --> 01:17:22.596
I'm not really
cut out for this anymore.

01:17:22.671 --> 01:17:26.300
I mean, a guy gets hit by a bus,
you know, and sues.

01:17:26.375 --> 01:17:27.672
l-I like that.

01:17:27.743 --> 01:17:30.871
Some lady, uh, slips in a supermarket.

01:17:30.946 --> 01:17:33.574
- I'm with her. A guy...
- The discussion's over.

01:17:33.649 --> 01:17:37.642
I'm an alcoholic. This is a murder case.
This isn't for me.

01:17:37.719 --> 01:17:40.085
- It was once.
- Yes, but...

01:17:40.155 --> 01:17:43.318
Before you let the drink lead.

01:17:43.392 --> 01:17:45.223
Be sober by tomorrow...

01:17:45.293 --> 01:17:47.454
and don't look so worried, Snyder.

01:17:47.529 --> 01:17:50.327
You got nothing to lose,
just like the rest of us.

01:17:50.399 --> 01:17:54.893
I don't want to be a burden to you,
but I do... You know, aside...

01:17:54.970 --> 01:17:58.997
Or along with my alcohol problem,
I have a-a-a slight drug problem.

01:17:59.074 --> 01:18:01.099
I mean, n-nothing big, just...

01:18:01.176 --> 01:18:03.440
Go away.

01:18:12.654 --> 01:18:14.417
Within days
of Michael taking the case...

01:18:14.489 --> 01:18:17.356
the West Side Boys
got a visit from King Benny.

01:18:17.426 --> 01:18:21.226
The king requested that the verbal abuse
directed towards Michael continue.

01:18:21.296 --> 01:18:24.595
Cries of <i>"</i> traitor" and <i>"</i> gutter rat"
were heard up and down the avenue...

01:18:24.666 --> 01:18:27.100
but there was never
to be a death move against him.

01:18:27.169 --> 01:18:29.660
The hit on Michael Sullivan,
if there was to be one...

01:18:29.738 --> 01:18:31.638
could only come from King Benny.

01:18:31.707 --> 01:18:34.198
The underground word...
the only one that mattered...

01:18:34.276 --> 01:18:37.040
had spread through the streets
with the speed of a late-night bullet.

01:18:41.516 --> 01:18:44.485
King Benny's sleepers
were making their play.

01:18:44.553 --> 01:18:46.043
<i>"</i> Sleepers" was a street name...

01:18:46.121 --> 01:18:48.954
for anyone who spent time
in a juvenile facility.

01:18:58.366 --> 01:19:00.994
Hey! You gonna pay for that,
you little prick?

01:19:01.069 --> 01:19:05.870
I need your help, Fat Man.
I need a big favor. Be outside.

01:19:05.941 --> 01:19:08.501
- King Benny been to see you?
- Oh, my goodness.

01:19:08.577 --> 01:19:11.137
What a fucking thing
we put together, huh?

01:19:11.213 --> 01:19:13.909
You have a drunk lawyer
on one side...

01:19:13.982 --> 01:19:15.813
a kid lawyer on the other...

01:19:15.884 --> 01:19:19.411
Fucking paperboy
making like Dick Tracy.

01:19:19.488 --> 01:19:23.424
There are four sets of eyeballs
that saw the whole thing. You know?

01:19:23.492 --> 01:19:26.620
Meanwhile, the two on trial
killed more people than cancer.

01:19:26.695 --> 01:19:28.993
Fucking General Custer
has a better shot at a walk.

01:19:29.064 --> 01:19:30.861
There's no connection
with the guard and us.

01:19:30.932 --> 01:19:32.729
The cops think
it's a drug-related homicide.

01:19:32.801 --> 01:19:34.962
It's just we need you
to pull a few strings, Fat Man.

01:19:35.036 --> 01:19:38.335
Dude, you get caught on this,
you're lookin' straight-ass serious.

01:19:38.406 --> 01:19:41.102
I'm talking real jail.
The big house.

01:19:43.278 --> 01:19:45.246
Hey, Mike.

01:19:48.083 --> 01:19:50.643
They are not good boys anymore.

01:19:50.719 --> 01:19:52.812
They're killers now.

01:19:52.888 --> 01:19:55.721
Cold as stone.

01:19:55.791 --> 01:19:57.190
I know.

01:19:57.259 --> 01:19:58.920
I know what they were
and I know what they are.

01:19:58.994 --> 01:20:00.484
And it's not about that.

01:20:00.562 --> 01:20:02.962
It's not worth it,
throwing away a life...

01:20:03.031 --> 01:20:05.499
just to get even.

01:20:05.567 --> 01:20:07.626
You and the lawyer
have a chance to get out...

01:20:07.702 --> 01:20:09.226
to get out the right way.

01:20:09.304 --> 01:20:12.137
There's no choice.
Not for us.

01:20:15.944 --> 01:20:17.878
On occasion,
I'd have dinner with Carol.

01:20:17.946 --> 01:20:22.315
She still lived in the neighborhood and
was a social worker in the South Bronx.

01:20:22.384 --> 01:20:25.512
Her concern for us
was undiminished by the passing years.

01:20:25.587 --> 01:20:27.077
Whenever we went out as a group...

01:20:27.155 --> 01:20:31.717
Carol would walk between Michael
and John, grasping their arms...

01:20:31.793 --> 01:20:33.920
in step between
the lawyer and the killer.

01:20:33.995 --> 01:20:36.122
Mug me or marry me, Shakes.

01:20:36.198 --> 01:20:38.826
I'm too tired for anything else.

01:20:38.900 --> 01:20:42.802
Would you settle
for a couple beers, Carol?

01:20:42.871 --> 01:20:44.702
If that's your best offer.

01:20:46.141 --> 01:20:48.666
I'll throw in a hug and a kiss.

01:20:48.743 --> 01:20:50.540
Deal.

01:20:55.684 --> 01:20:58.847
- You look tired.
- Thank you.

01:20:58.920 --> 01:21:01.286
They don't give you time to sleep
in this new job of yours?

01:21:01.356 --> 01:21:05.986
<i>What a very special time for me</i>

01:21:06.061 --> 01:21:08.427
So how much do you know?

01:21:08.496 --> 01:21:11.056
Just what the neighborhood says...

01:21:11.132 --> 01:21:13.896
or what I read
in papers like yours.

01:21:13.969 --> 01:21:15.561
What does the neighborhood say?

01:21:15.637 --> 01:21:17.628
That they're gonna
putJohnny and Tommy away.

01:21:17.706 --> 01:21:19.970
That their best friend's
gonna be the one to do it.

01:21:20.041 --> 01:21:22.805
- You believe that?
- It's hard not to, Shakes.

01:21:22.878 --> 01:21:24.812
Unless we all have it wrong.

01:21:24.880 --> 01:21:27.610
He did take the fuckin' case.

01:21:27.682 --> 01:21:29.946
- He did take the case.
- What else is there to say?

01:21:32.754 --> 01:21:34.847
You know Michael very well.

01:21:34.923 --> 01:21:36.857
Maybe even better than I do.

01:21:36.925 --> 01:21:39.359
Yeah, I thought I did.
Now I don't know.

01:21:39.427 --> 01:21:41.918
- You do know.
- I don't know!

01:21:41.997 --> 01:21:43.658
He went in there
and he asked for the case.

01:21:43.732 --> 01:21:46.792
Now you tell me.
What the hell kind of friend is that?

01:21:46.868 --> 01:21:49.098
The best kind.

01:21:49.170 --> 01:21:51.934
The kind that'd throw away everything
to help his friends.

01:21:55.610 --> 01:21:57.544
What are you tellin' me, Shakes?

01:21:58.580 --> 01:22:00.309
You know this neighborhood, Carol.

01:22:00.382 --> 01:22:04.182
Everything's a shakedown or a scam.
Why should this be any different?

01:22:10.659 --> 01:22:13.025
I'm hungry.

01:22:13.094 --> 01:22:16.029
I'm gonna get somethin' to eat.

01:22:16.097 --> 01:22:18.156
There's this point in Michael...

01:22:18.233 --> 01:22:20.258
that you can't go beyond.

01:22:20.335 --> 01:22:21.768
I mean, you can try.

01:22:21.836 --> 01:22:23.463
I tried...

01:22:23.538 --> 01:22:26.905
and he just shut down.

01:22:26.975 --> 01:22:30.706
Couldn't touch him.
Couldn't even breathe on him.

01:22:33.281 --> 01:22:35.215
I thought it was me.

01:22:36.952 --> 01:22:39.944
After a while,
it just gets easy to let it go.

01:22:40.021 --> 01:22:43.149
- You still love him?
- I don't think about it, Shakes.

01:22:44.659 --> 01:22:47.059
If I did, I'd say <i>"</i> yes."

01:22:47.128 --> 01:22:48.891
But you're with John now.

01:22:48.964 --> 01:22:54.266
Yeah. As much as anybody
can be with John.

01:22:55.737 --> 01:22:57.568
The man I know
is not the boy you remember.

01:22:57.639 --> 01:23:00.073
None of us are.

01:23:00.141 --> 01:23:02.609
But there's somethin' special
aboutJohn.

01:23:03.878 --> 01:23:06.813
You just have to look
a little harder to see it.

01:23:06.881 --> 01:23:09.247
Yeah.

01:23:11.252 --> 01:23:13.186
Why didn't you ever ask me out?

01:23:13.254 --> 01:23:15.722
- Me?
- Yeah.

01:23:16.725 --> 01:23:18.750
'Cause you were Mikey's girl.

01:23:20.695 --> 01:23:23.459
- He got to you first.
- And after Mikey?

01:23:24.466 --> 01:23:27.594
- I think it was Tommy's turn.
- Oh, fuck you!

01:23:29.537 --> 01:23:32.131
I don't know. It was, uh...

01:23:33.141 --> 01:23:37.271
l-I didn't think
you'd say yes, and, uh...

01:23:41.816 --> 01:23:44.910
Well, you were wrong, Shakes.

01:23:45.520 --> 01:23:47.454
You were wrong.

01:23:53.094 --> 01:23:55.824
What? Go ahead, say it.

01:23:56.965 --> 01:23:58.227
You work at social services.

01:23:58.299 --> 01:24:00.529
You got files...
You got access to files...

01:24:00.602 --> 01:24:02.934
and from time to time
we're gonna need some information.

01:24:03.004 --> 01:24:05.598
Yeah. Sure. Whatever.

01:24:05.673 --> 01:24:07.868
Wait. What?

01:24:07.942 --> 01:24:09.671
What? What do you want?
Y-You want information?

01:24:09.744 --> 01:24:11.473
Y-You want me to get the files,
I get the files.

01:24:11.546 --> 01:24:14.811
- No, I didn't want. I didn't...
- What do you want?

01:24:20.088 --> 01:24:22.056
You still visitJohn?

01:24:22.123 --> 01:24:23.920
Yeah. Once a week
for about an hour.

01:24:23.992 --> 01:24:26.222
- Good.
- Good?

01:24:26.294 --> 01:24:29.786
Yeah, good. Just don't tell him
that you've seen me.

01:24:29.864 --> 01:24:31.024
Don't tell him anything.

01:24:31.099 --> 01:24:34.091
The more he thinks this thing's
hopeless, the better it might work.

01:24:35.136 --> 01:24:38.594
Shakes, what is this about?

01:24:39.506 --> 01:24:42.805
If you want a Rolls-Royce,
you don't come here.

01:24:42.876 --> 01:24:45.743
You go to England
or wherever the fuck they make it.

01:24:45.812 --> 01:24:47.780
If you want champagne,
you go see the French.

01:24:47.847 --> 01:24:50.042
If you need money,
you find a Jew.

01:24:50.116 --> 01:24:54.052
But if you want dirt or scum
buried under a rock somewhere...

01:24:54.120 --> 01:24:56.554
or some secret nobody
wants anybody to know about...

01:24:56.623 --> 01:25:00.059
there's only one place to go...
right here, Hell's Kitchen.

01:25:00.126 --> 01:25:03.220
It is the lost and found of shit.

01:25:03.296 --> 01:25:06.595
They lose it and we find it.
Forget about it, man.

01:25:07.901 --> 01:25:11.598
Now you only got two witnesses
who are gonna testify.

01:25:12.439 --> 01:25:16.102
- Two others changed their minds.
- Which two?

01:25:16.176 --> 01:25:19.373
The suits at the bar.

01:25:19.446 --> 01:25:21.744
So that still leaves
the couple in the booth.

01:25:21.815 --> 01:25:24.579
For now.

01:25:24.651 --> 01:25:27.586
Everything else fallin' into place?

01:25:27.654 --> 01:25:30.145
Except for your witness.

01:25:30.223 --> 01:25:32.783
That pocket's still empty.

01:25:32.859 --> 01:25:34.793
I know.

01:25:38.231 --> 01:25:41.029
When you were sent away...

01:25:41.101 --> 01:25:43.968
I was always sorry
I couldn't do more for you.

01:25:52.412 --> 01:25:54.937
I didn't know
you liked pigeons so much.

01:25:55.015 --> 01:25:57.848
I like anything that don't talk.

01:25:58.685 --> 01:26:01.711
Michael's vision of where he wanted
this case to go was very clear.

01:26:01.788 --> 01:26:03.722
He was aiming for guilty...

01:26:03.790 --> 01:26:06.258
a charge of guilty against
the Wilkinson Home for Boys...

01:26:06.326 --> 01:26:10.729
against Sean Nokes, Adam Styler,
Henry Addison and Ralph Ferguson.

01:26:10.797 --> 01:26:14.631
I will present you evidence and offer
into account testimony to prove that.

01:26:14.701 --> 01:26:16.760
I will place him
at the scene of the crime.

01:26:16.836 --> 01:26:19.828
I will bring witnesses to the stand
who will confirm...

01:26:19.906 --> 01:26:22.272
that they were there
on that deadly night.

01:26:22.342 --> 01:26:25.971
I will present enough evidence
that you can then go into a jury room...

01:26:26.046 --> 01:26:29.709
and come back with a clear decision
that's beyond a reasonable doubt.

01:26:30.617 --> 01:26:34.383
I'm sure you all know what that means,
since you probably watch as much
television as I do.

01:26:37.424 --> 01:26:39.824
John. John Reilly...

01:26:39.893 --> 01:26:43.226
and Thomas Marcano are two
innocent pawns quickly arrested...

01:26:43.296 --> 01:26:47.926
and just, uh, as,
uh, quickly prosecuted...

01:26:48.001 --> 01:26:50.731
on the slightest threads of evidence.

01:26:50.804 --> 01:26:53.739
On the bright side,
he seems to know their names.

01:27:05.385 --> 01:27:07.751
It's nice when you come around.

01:27:10.123 --> 01:27:13.115
Hey, bring me another spoon.
This one's dirty.

01:27:13.193 --> 01:27:15.684
- Take it.
- No, no. She'll do it.

01:27:24.504 --> 01:27:26.438
So how's work?

01:27:28.108 --> 01:27:30.042
I'm still there.

01:27:33.480 --> 01:27:38.975
You know, Pop, l, uh...
I went down to the courthouse.

01:27:39.052 --> 01:27:40.986
John and Tommy...
I saw John and Tommy...

01:27:41.054 --> 01:27:44.182
and, uh, suddenly I started
thinking back to when we...

01:27:44.257 --> 01:27:46.191
Well, where's the chicken?

01:27:49.596 --> 01:27:52.360
So?

01:27:52.432 --> 01:27:56.869
Nothin'.
I was just thinkin' things.

01:27:56.936 --> 01:27:59.632
But you're doin' good, right?

01:27:59.706 --> 01:28:02.174
Oh, yeah. I'm good.

01:28:02.242 --> 01:28:04.176
Good.

01:28:46.052 --> 01:28:48.543
- What the hell do these things do?
- They're for praying.

01:28:48.621 --> 01:28:52.819
Just look at all this shit.
Does your mother think you're
in the fuckin' army or somethin'?

01:28:52.892 --> 01:28:56.419
- Ain't none of it on the approved list.
- Sure your mommy got a copy
of that list?

01:28:56.496 --> 01:28:58.123
My mother
can't speak English that well.

01:28:58.198 --> 01:29:01.463
Oh, don't blame us for your fuckin'
mother bein' stupid, all right?

01:29:06.539 --> 01:29:09.133
When are you gonna let us
hear you pray?

01:29:19.385 --> 01:29:21.512
Maybe he needs somethin'
to pray for.

01:29:21.588 --> 01:29:25.354
Put your hands on the table
and lay 'em down flat.

01:29:25.425 --> 01:29:27.859
Spread your legs.

01:29:27.927 --> 01:29:31.727
Start thinkin' up some prayers.

01:29:40.039 --> 01:29:43.497
- We don't hear no prayin'.
- You better start, else Styler
might lose his baton up your ass.

01:29:43.576 --> 01:29:47.706
Blessed art thou among women and
blessed is the fruit of thy wombJesus.

01:29:47.780 --> 01:29:50.749
- Pray nice and loud.
- Hail Mary, full of grace...

01:29:50.817 --> 01:29:52.682
Now louder!

01:29:52.752 --> 01:29:54.845
Fuckin' pray! Come on now!

01:29:56.589 --> 01:29:59.581
- Louder!
- Can't hear you!

01:30:00.059 --> 01:30:01.720
Louder, fucker!

01:30:03.596 --> 01:30:05.757
Pray till your balls hurt!

01:30:08.768 --> 01:30:10.395
Louder!

01:30:16.376 --> 01:30:18.844
Sorry I'm late.
I lost all track of time.

01:30:18.911 --> 01:30:21.436
I got this idea for a witness,
but I'm not quite sure yet.

01:30:21.514 --> 01:30:24.745
But I wanted you to come along
so you could see it.

01:30:26.052 --> 01:30:28.213
- Where are we going?
- To his place.

01:30:28.288 --> 01:30:30.222
- Where is it?
- He's in the rectory.

01:30:30.290 --> 01:30:34.226
No, Shakes. I can't...

01:30:40.533 --> 01:30:43.195
How was court today?

01:30:43.269 --> 01:30:47.638
Like the first round of a fight...
everybody just feelin' each other out.

01:30:48.975 --> 01:30:51.136
How did the boys look?

01:30:51.210 --> 01:30:53.303
Like they wished
they was someplace else.

01:30:54.814 --> 01:30:57.840
It's the sheep that stray
that you most want back.

01:30:59.552 --> 01:31:01.577
It's not too late, Father.

01:31:03.756 --> 01:31:07.419
We still have a chance to bring in
a couple of stray sheep.

01:31:07.493 --> 01:31:09.427
One more chance.

01:31:11.164 --> 01:31:13.098
Is that chance legal?

01:31:14.834 --> 01:31:16.859
Last chances never are.

01:31:16.936 --> 01:31:19.803
King Benny behind this?

01:31:19.872 --> 01:31:23.137
He's in on it, but, uh,
he's not callin' the shots.

01:31:23.209 --> 01:31:26.269
- Who is?
- Michael.

01:31:28.348 --> 01:31:30.612
I should've smelled it.

01:31:30.683 --> 01:31:33.584
The minute he went for the case,
I should've figured somethin' was up.

01:31:33.653 --> 01:31:36.918
It's a good plan.
Michael's got it all covered.

01:31:36.989 --> 01:31:40.083
Just about every base you look at,
he... he's got it covered.

01:31:40.159 --> 01:31:42.491
Not every base.

01:31:42.562 --> 01:31:44.826
You're short something,
or else you wouldn't be here.

01:31:44.897 --> 01:31:46.990
You don't shit a shitter, right?

01:31:47.066 --> 01:31:49.000
That's right.

01:31:50.570 --> 01:31:54.097
So what is it?
Where do you come up short?

01:31:55.308 --> 01:31:59.711
Witness. We need
somebody to take the stand...

01:31:59.779 --> 01:32:02.247
and say they were with John and Tommy
on the night of the murder.

01:32:02.315 --> 01:32:04.647
So you figured if you had a priest,
it would be perfect.

01:32:05.551 --> 01:32:08.281
Not just any priest.

01:32:19.065 --> 01:32:21.363
So you're...

01:32:23.403 --> 01:32:26.702
you're asking me...

01:32:26.773 --> 01:32:29.537
you're asking me to lie.

01:32:29.609 --> 01:32:32.976
You're asking me to swear to God
and then lie.

01:32:33.045 --> 01:32:35.912
I'm asking you to save
two of your boys.

01:32:40.920 --> 01:32:45.357
- Did they kill that guard?
- Yes.

01:32:45.425 --> 01:32:49.418
So what they said is true.
They walked in and they killed him.

01:32:50.530 --> 01:32:53.363
Yes.

01:32:53.433 --> 01:32:56.061
They killed him exactly like that.

01:32:59.172 --> 01:33:01.265
I think I need a drink.

01:33:02.909 --> 01:33:05.901
Anyone want a drink?

01:33:05.978 --> 01:33:07.775
Yeah.

01:33:22.528 --> 01:33:24.860
This is some favor
you're asking me.

01:33:25.765 --> 01:33:30.293
- We know that.
- No, I don't think you do know.

01:33:31.304 --> 01:33:33.602
You said if there was ever
anything really important...

01:33:33.673 --> 01:33:36.039
I could come to you, ask you.

01:33:36.108 --> 01:33:40.010
I was thinking more
along the lines of Yankee tickets.

01:33:41.214 --> 01:33:46.618
I don't need Yankee tickets, Father.
I need a witness.

01:33:47.487 --> 01:33:51.150
What about the life that was taken,
Shakes? What's that worth?

01:33:51.224 --> 01:33:54.819
To me? Nothing.

01:33:56.496 --> 01:33:59.693
Why not? Tell me.

01:34:05.471 --> 01:34:08.338
He was a...

01:34:08.407 --> 01:34:11.171
He was a guard at Wilkinson's.

01:34:13.579 --> 01:34:15.012
All right?

01:34:15.081 --> 01:34:17.015
If Father Bobby
was gonna be involved...

01:34:17.083 --> 01:34:19.313
he deserved to know
what he was getting into.

01:34:19.385 --> 01:34:22.320
If he wasn't, I trusted that the
truth would go no further than his room.

01:34:23.890 --> 01:34:26.484
I thought that Carol
needed to know as well.

01:34:26.559 --> 01:34:28.493
Jesus Christ,
we were just boys.

01:34:28.561 --> 01:34:30.529
We weren't that tough.

01:34:33.466 --> 01:34:35.661
They held us down.

01:34:38.571 --> 01:34:42.803
I told him about the torture,
the beatings and the rapes.

01:34:42.875 --> 01:34:45.036
I told him about
the four frightened boys...

01:34:45.111 --> 01:34:48.410
who prayed to Father Bobby's god
for help that never came.

01:34:48.481 --> 01:34:50.312
I told him everything.

01:34:50.383 --> 01:34:52.442
And you can't...
you can't fight anymore.

01:34:52.518 --> 01:34:56.921
You just took it all.
John used to wail at night.

01:34:56.989 --> 01:35:00.049
You'd hear it
all the way down the hall.

01:35:01.627 --> 01:35:04.858
You know he wanted to be a priest.
John wanted to be a priest.

01:35:16.375 --> 01:35:18.502
I just sort of blacked out,
but what I could remember...

01:35:18.578 --> 01:35:20.876
is that I couldn't even breathe.

01:35:22.381 --> 01:35:24.713
I started to choke...

01:35:29.322 --> 01:35:31.415
Then I blacked out.

01:35:33.059 --> 01:35:35.926
But I do remember when...
when, for fun...

01:35:35.995 --> 01:35:38.589
they'd take us down in the basement...

01:35:38.664 --> 01:35:42.122
and tie two or three of us
together and watch.

01:36:00.219 --> 01:36:03.017
I got a decision to make.

01:36:06.692 --> 01:36:09.092
I only pray it's the right one.

01:36:10.262 --> 01:36:14.164
It will be, Father,
whichever way you go.

01:36:19.705 --> 01:36:21.639
Good night.

01:36:29.615 --> 01:36:33.244
Okay, so you were sitting down,
you were having dinner...

01:36:33.319 --> 01:36:35.913
- And two men entered McHale's, correct?
- Yes.

01:36:35.988 --> 01:36:39.151
Did you see the two men
as they approached the table
where Mr. Nokes was sitting?

01:36:39.225 --> 01:36:41.284
l-I noticed it, yes.

01:36:41.360 --> 01:36:44.295
- Did you hear
what was said between them?
- Um, no.

01:36:44.363 --> 01:36:46.729
- Did you see them pull out their guns?
- No.

01:36:46.799 --> 01:36:50.565
- Did you hear the shots?
- Yes, I heard the shots.

01:36:50.636 --> 01:36:54.902
And what did they do? What was their
behavior after... after the shooting?

01:36:55.941 --> 01:36:58.967
They walked out of McHale's
as if nothing had happened.

01:36:59.045 --> 01:37:04.108
And at that time, Mrs. Salinas,
did you see their faces clearly?

01:37:04.817 --> 01:37:08.548
Yes. I looked up
as they walked away.

01:37:08.621 --> 01:37:11.454
- Are you positive?
- Yes. Very positive.

01:37:11.524 --> 01:37:14.322
And are the two men you saw in McHale's,
are they in this room today?

01:37:14.393 --> 01:37:17.692
- Yes, they are.
- Could you point them out
for the jury, please?

01:37:18.798 --> 01:37:21.358
They're sitting right over there.

01:37:21.434 --> 01:37:24.835
Your Honor, will the record reflect
that Mrs. Salinas has identified...

01:37:24.904 --> 01:37:29.102
defendants John Reilly and Thomas
Marcano as the two men in question.

01:37:29.175 --> 01:37:31.973
- Noted.
- Thank you. No further questions.

01:37:32.378 --> 01:37:35.575
Counsel, are you ready to proceed?

01:37:35.648 --> 01:37:38.173
Yes, Your Honor, we are.
Good morning.

01:37:38.250 --> 01:37:42.482
I just have a few questions.
I won't take too much
of your time, Mrs. Salinas.

01:37:42.555 --> 01:37:46.685
Uh, you stated that, uh, you
only had wine to drink with dinner.

01:37:46.759 --> 01:37:48.693
- Is that correct?
- Yes.
- Are you sure about that?

01:37:48.761 --> 01:37:53.130
Are you sure that's all you had...
one, uh, bottle of wine?

01:37:53.199 --> 01:37:55.497
- Yes. A bottle of red Chianti.
- Uh-huh.

01:37:55.568 --> 01:37:58.560
Had you anything to drink,
uh, prior to that?

01:37:58.637 --> 01:38:02.300
- What do you mean, prior?
- At, uh, uh, lunch.

01:38:02.374 --> 01:38:04.638
Maybe did you have anything
to drink at lunch?

01:38:04.710 --> 01:38:07.702
- Yes, I did.
- And, uh, what did you have to drink?

01:38:07.780 --> 01:38:10.044
I went shopping, and l, um...

01:38:10.116 --> 01:38:12.550
I stopped at a place
on Madison Avenue for some...

01:38:12.618 --> 01:38:15.587
See, I didn't ask you where you went.
I asked you what you had
to drink at lunch.

01:38:16.655 --> 01:38:18.919
- A martini.
- And what else?

01:38:20.826 --> 01:38:23.693
Um, probably some wine.

01:38:23.763 --> 01:38:29.201
Yes, and how... Uh, how many, uh,
glasses of wine did you have to drink?

01:38:29.268 --> 01:38:32.499
Um, one-one glass, maybe two.

01:38:33.172 --> 01:38:37.074
- Closer to two?
- Yes. Probably two glasses. About two.

01:38:37.143 --> 01:38:41.546
And did you, uh, uh...

01:38:42.214 --> 01:38:44.273
It's like pulling teeth.

01:38:44.350 --> 01:38:46.079
Uh...

01:38:46.152 --> 01:38:49.019
I should've pinned
the questions to his shirt.

01:38:49.088 --> 01:38:53.286
And, uh, tell me, uh,
then at dinner, you, uh...

01:38:53.359 --> 01:38:56.760
Uh... Strike that. Uh...

01:38:58.764 --> 01:39:01.232
Uh, uh...

01:39:03.102 --> 01:39:05.627
What time, Mrs. Salinas,
did you have lunch?

01:39:05.704 --> 01:39:08.172
Objection, Your Honor.

01:39:08.240 --> 01:39:10.640
What Mrs. Salinas did
on the day of the murder...

01:39:10.709 --> 01:39:12.973
has nothing to do with what
she saw on the night of the murder.

01:39:13.045 --> 01:39:15.980
- How much she had
to drink does, Your Honor.
- Overruled.

01:39:17.917 --> 01:39:21.375
Mrs. Salinas, what time,
uh, did you have lunch?

01:39:21.453 --> 01:39:24.752
- About 1:30.
- And what did you have for lunch?

01:39:24.824 --> 01:39:27.952
It was a while ago.
Um, probably a salad.

01:39:28.027 --> 01:39:30.427
l-I like to eat
a little light in the day.

01:39:30.496 --> 01:39:32.794
A martini, two glasses of wine
and a salad.

01:39:32.865 --> 01:39:35.390
- Is that correct?
- Yes. That's right.

01:39:35.467 --> 01:39:39.130
And then you had wine at dinner
about six hours later.

01:39:39.205 --> 01:39:41.696
- Is that right?
- Yes, that's right.

01:39:41.774 --> 01:39:45.608
How much wine did you have to drink
by the time my clients
allegedly walked into McHale's?

01:39:45.678 --> 01:39:48.613
- Two glasses.
- Would you say that, uh...

01:39:48.681 --> 01:39:52.845
four glasses of wine and a martini
within a six-hour period...

01:39:52.918 --> 01:39:55.978
- Is a lot for you to drink?
- Yes, it is. Yes.

01:39:56.055 --> 01:39:58.751
Uh-huh. Sure.

01:39:58.824 --> 01:40:02.282
Uh... And, uh...

01:40:02.361 --> 01:40:07.060
had you ever heard a gun fired
prior to the night in question?

01:40:07.132 --> 01:40:09.293
No.

01:40:09.368 --> 01:40:11.962
Uh, how would you
describe the sound?

01:40:12.037 --> 01:40:14.471
It's loud,
like fireworks loud.

01:40:15.908 --> 01:40:20.174
- Did the sound, uh, frighten you?
- Very much.

01:40:20.246 --> 01:40:22.806
Did you close your...
uh, your eyes?

01:40:24.016 --> 01:40:27.850
At first, um, until the shooting
stopped, then I opened them.

01:40:27.920 --> 01:40:31.651
Did you think the men who did
the shooting were going to kill
everybody in McHale's?

01:40:31.724 --> 01:40:33.783
Well, l-I really didn't know
what to think.

01:40:33.859 --> 01:40:36.020
l-I just knew
that a man had been shot.

01:40:36.095 --> 01:40:40.964
Did you think you might be shot dead
by the two cold-blooded killers?

01:40:41.567 --> 01:40:43.330
Yes. Yes, I did.

01:40:43.402 --> 01:40:47.634
Yet, despite that fear,
despite that, uh, risk to your life...

01:40:47.706 --> 01:40:52.200
you looked at their faces,
uh, as they left?

01:40:52.278 --> 01:40:54.405
- Yes, I did.
- Is that correct?

01:40:55.848 --> 01:40:58.646
- Yes, I did.
- Did you look at their faces?

01:40:58.717 --> 01:41:03.984
Did you really, really look,
Mrs. Salinas?

01:41:04.990 --> 01:41:07.686
I glanced at them when they walked by,
but I did see them.

01:41:07.760 --> 01:41:12.026
You glanced. You didn't look.

01:41:13.065 --> 01:41:15.124
I saw them.

01:41:15.200 --> 01:41:18.101
You glanced at them,
Mrs. Salinas.

01:41:18.170 --> 01:41:21.970
You glanced at them through the eyes
of a very frightened woman...

01:41:22.041 --> 01:41:25.340
who maybe had too much to drink.

01:41:25.411 --> 01:41:27.208
Objection, Your Honor.

01:41:27.279 --> 01:41:30.112
There is no need, Your Honor.
I have no further questions.

01:41:30.182 --> 01:41:32.946
Thank you, Mrs. Salinas.
You may step down.

01:41:36.388 --> 01:41:38.879
It was 6:15 on Sunday morning.

01:41:38.958 --> 01:41:42.155
Frank Magcicco worked
out of a homicide unit in Brooklyn.

01:41:42.227 --> 01:41:45.856
He was a first-rate detective with
an honest name and a solid reputation.

01:41:45.931 --> 01:41:48.365
He was also King Benny's nephew.

01:41:48.434 --> 01:41:51.335
Nick Davenport
was with internal affairs.

01:41:51.403 --> 01:41:54.429
He was ambitious and wanted
to make captain before he hit 40.

01:41:54.506 --> 01:41:56.531
He knew the fastest way up the track
was to reel in...

01:41:56.608 --> 01:42:00.203
a maximum amount of dirty cops
in a minimum amount of time.

01:42:00.279 --> 01:42:02.304
- Frank, what is this shit?
- Hey, I were you...

01:42:02.381 --> 01:42:04.849
I'd do what the kid says.
You make this one...

01:42:04.917 --> 01:42:07.385
you're gonna be having breakfast
once a month with the commissioner.

01:42:07.453 --> 01:42:10.251
Man, you got a real hard-on
for this style of guy, huh?

01:42:10.322 --> 01:42:12.517
- What's your beef with him?
- One more thing.

01:42:12.591 --> 01:42:15.059
- I can't wait.
- It's simple.

01:42:15.127 --> 01:42:17.425
No one knows if I give you
this information.

01:42:17.496 --> 01:42:19.430
- And I mean nobody.
- How did you get it?

01:42:19.498 --> 01:42:23.093
It fell into my lap,
just like it's gonna fall into yours.

01:42:30.142 --> 01:42:32.235
Christ almighty!

01:42:38.917 --> 01:42:42.580
- Got everything in here
but a confession.
- I thought I'd leave that up to you.

01:42:42.654 --> 01:42:46.317
- My preference is
that you beat it out of him.
- There's even surveillance photos.

01:42:46.392 --> 01:42:49.987
This piece of shit's pullin' in about
five grand a month rippin' off pushers.

01:42:50.062 --> 01:42:52.895
- Has been for about three years.
- More like four.

01:42:52.965 --> 01:42:55.126
- He ain't gonna see five.
- So you got enough for a conviction?

01:42:55.200 --> 01:42:57.430
That ain't up to me.
That's up to a jury.

01:43:01.140 --> 01:43:04.109
Show the jury this.

01:43:04.176 --> 01:43:08.374
- Well, what do you got there, Ness?
- About three weeks ago...

01:43:08.447 --> 01:43:10.847
the body of a drug dealer
named Indian Red Lopez...

01:43:10.916 --> 01:43:12.850
was found in an alley
in Jackson Heights...

01:43:12.918 --> 01:43:15.318
three bullets in his head,
nothing in his pockets.

01:43:15.387 --> 01:43:17.855
- I'm with you so far.
- This is the gun that killed him...

01:43:17.923 --> 01:43:19.857
and these are the shells.

01:43:19.925 --> 01:43:22.723
And, uh, what's behind
door number three?

01:43:23.295 --> 01:43:25.855
The prints on the gun
belong to Adam Styler.

01:43:29.635 --> 01:43:32.365
- Hey, do me a favor, would you?
- What's that?

01:43:32.438 --> 01:43:35.134
If I ever make it onto your shit list,
give me a call.

01:43:35.207 --> 01:43:37.607
Give me a chance to apologize.

01:43:37.676 --> 01:43:40.008
So, you need anything else,
you talk to Frank.

01:43:40.079 --> 01:43:43.674
- He knows how to get a hold of me.
- Take care of yourself, kid.

01:43:43.749 --> 01:43:46.877
- The water gets choppy out your way.
- I'll do what I can.

01:43:48.020 --> 01:43:52.423
Hey, Ness. Did you ever think
of becomin' a cop?

01:43:52.491 --> 01:43:54.425
And leave the good guys?

01:44:04.970 --> 01:44:06.767
The body of Christ.

01:44:08.373 --> 01:44:11.536
- The body of Christ.
- Amen.

01:44:11.610 --> 01:44:13.737
- The body of Christ.
- Amen.

01:44:15.747 --> 01:44:18.215
- The body of Christ.
- Amen.

01:44:20.018 --> 01:44:22.384
- The body of Christ.
- Amen.

01:44:22.454 --> 01:44:25.014
The body of Chri...

01:44:33.332 --> 01:44:35.232
Amen.

01:44:37.569 --> 01:44:39.867
The body of Christ.

01:44:42.374 --> 01:44:44.934
Michael had done
all that could be expected...

01:44:45.010 --> 01:44:48.241
of an assistant district attorney
seeking a conviction.

01:44:48.313 --> 01:44:51.282
He had a forensic expert
detail the make and caliber...

01:44:51.350 --> 01:44:53.409
of the gun that killed Nokes.

01:44:53.485 --> 01:44:55.976
He just never had the murder weapon
to present as evidence...

01:44:56.054 --> 01:44:59.512
and he never gave the jury
a motive for the murder.

01:44:59.591 --> 01:45:02.526
The tension of his task,
the hours he was working...

01:45:02.594 --> 01:45:05.427
and the uncertainty about the outcome
weighed heavily on him.

01:45:05.497 --> 01:45:08.295
- Did you see their faces?
- Yes. I looked at them...

01:45:08.367 --> 01:45:11.302
- And they looked at me.
- Did they say anything to you?

01:45:11.370 --> 01:45:13.736
No. They just looked at me
and walked out of McHale's.

01:45:13.805 --> 01:45:16.069
Are you sure the two defendants
killed Sean Nokes?

01:45:16.141 --> 01:45:17.938
I know they killed him.

01:45:18.010 --> 01:45:21.138
If the plan worked,
it would be everyone's success.

01:45:21.213 --> 01:45:23.738
If it failed, the fault
would fall on Michael.

01:45:23.815 --> 01:45:25.476
Oh, boy, man!

01:45:26.585 --> 01:45:30.954
Father Bobby Carillo, the priest with
the best hook shot on the west side...

01:45:31.023 --> 01:45:35.016
remained the key to a plan
that called for all involved
to get away with murder.

01:45:35.093 --> 01:45:38.824
Did you turn around, look behind you
when you heard the shooting, Mr. Carson?

01:45:38.897 --> 01:45:42.230
- Why-Why didn't you
turn around, Mr. Carson?
- I was concerned for my...

01:45:42.301 --> 01:45:46.863
- Mr. Carson, did the two individuals
threaten you in any way?
- No.

01:45:46.939 --> 01:45:51.501
Did they threaten anyone in
McHale's Restaurant as far as you know?

01:45:51.577 --> 01:45:53.511
I didn't see it, but I know it.

01:45:53.579 --> 01:45:56.047
If you didn't see the defendants
shoot the guys...

01:45:56.114 --> 01:45:59.675
then how do you know it was
the defendants that shot the guy?

01:46:21.873 --> 01:46:23.864
So what's the emergency?

01:46:27.479 --> 01:46:29.743
You know, Shakes shouldn't
have sent you. It's too risky.

01:46:29.815 --> 01:46:33.080
Hey, nobody sent me.
I wanted to see you.

01:46:35.187 --> 01:46:37.781
Why?

01:46:37.856 --> 01:46:40.848
Shakes met with Father Bobby
two weeks ago.

01:46:40.926 --> 01:46:45.329
- He hasn't heard from him since.
- It's not an overnight decision
for him.

01:46:47.766 --> 01:46:51.964
- What if he doesn't testify?
- Then we got a very serious problem.

01:47:06.118 --> 01:47:09.519
Ha... Have Shakes talk
to Father Bobby again.

01:47:10.789 --> 01:47:14.384
Have him tell him the whole story.
He'll know what that means.

01:47:14.459 --> 01:47:19.055
- He already has.
- What?

01:47:19.131 --> 01:47:23.864
l-I wa... I was with him
when he talked to Father Bobby.

01:47:26.204 --> 01:47:28.570
I heard everything, Michael.

01:47:38.450 --> 01:47:41.078
So you know.

01:47:42.454 --> 01:47:44.388
Yeah.

01:47:47.626 --> 01:47:49.753
If only you'd told me.

01:47:52.264 --> 01:47:56.200
l... I think things
could have been different.

01:47:58.537 --> 01:48:01.062
If you could've talked.

01:48:05.077 --> 01:48:08.569
Maybe... Maybe we...

01:48:11.350 --> 01:48:13.284
Maybe...

01:48:18.790 --> 01:48:21.258
I don't...

01:48:33.772 --> 01:48:36.263
- Spill 'em, you know?
- Right.

01:48:36.341 --> 01:48:38.400
Hey, Shay, how ya doin'?

01:48:38.477 --> 01:48:41.640
Oh, man, that diet is working.
I don't care what anybody says.

01:48:42.881 --> 01:48:46.874
- You still have a thing for Doris Day?
- She's a good woman.

01:48:48.253 --> 01:48:50.813
You know Lastrega?

01:48:50.889 --> 01:48:54.086
Hard to miss a lady
with four warts and only one eye.

01:48:54.159 --> 01:48:57.959
She needs the heads.
Salvatore.

01:49:01.633 --> 01:49:04.193
Take this to the witch.

01:49:04.970 --> 01:49:08.133
- Now, why does she need the heads?
- She takes the eyes.

01:49:08.206 --> 01:49:10.140
Oh. Wonderful.

01:49:10.208 --> 01:49:13.644
Puts them in a bowl
and mixes them with water and oil.

01:49:13.712 --> 01:49:15.304
And then?

01:49:16.648 --> 01:49:19.742
People get headaches,
they go to her.

01:49:19.818 --> 01:49:24.846
She looks into their eyes and tells them
who is wishing the headaches.

01:49:24.923 --> 01:49:29.383
She says a few words,
and the headaches go away.

01:49:29.461 --> 01:49:33.830
Once in a while, the person who
wished the headaches goes away too.

01:49:33.899 --> 01:49:38.563
This guy Addison,
the one who works for the mayor...

01:49:38.637 --> 01:49:41.435
he quits his job in two weeks.

01:49:41.506 --> 01:49:45.067
He don't want nobody to know
what kind of a guy he is.

01:49:45.143 --> 01:49:49.546
He don't want nobody to see pictures
of him they shouldn't see.

01:49:49.614 --> 01:49:52.879
- He knows us?
- He will.

01:49:52.951 --> 01:49:55.476
The boys he buys for parties
are expensive.

01:49:55.554 --> 01:50:00.389
Now, Addison makes good money,
but he don't make real money.

01:50:00.459 --> 01:50:04.759
- How much does he owe?
- Eight grand with a heavy vig.

01:50:04.830 --> 01:50:08.061
- I paid that off.
- You paid?

01:50:08.133 --> 01:50:11.796
Addison's debts belong to me now.

01:50:11.870 --> 01:50:14.896
- You hate debts.
- I hate Addison.

01:50:16.942 --> 01:50:20.776
We're in the dirty end of the field now.
That's where I play.

01:50:20.846 --> 01:50:25.112
And I like to play alone.
You're a nice kid. You always were.

01:50:26.117 --> 01:50:29.314
Don't let this change it. Go.

01:50:40.899 --> 01:50:45.996
His mother named him Edward Goldenberg
Robinson, after her favorite actor.

01:50:46.071 --> 01:50:49.529
To continue the Hollywood connection,
Eddie Robinson took the street name...

01:50:49.608 --> 01:50:54.375
" Little Caesar" as he made his way up
the ranks of the lucrative drug trade.

01:50:54.446 --> 01:50:58.246
He had a 12-year-old son in
a private school in upstate New York.

01:50:58.316 --> 01:51:00.944
He named him Rizzo,
after his youngest brother...

01:51:01.019 --> 01:51:04.284
who died while in the custody
of the Wilkinson Home for Boys.

01:51:04.356 --> 01:51:07.257
I want you to give me some money.

01:51:07.325 --> 01:51:12.319
All right. I'll play along.
How long before you pay it back?

01:51:12.397 --> 01:51:15.924
I ain't paying it back.
Somebody else is.

01:51:18.169 --> 01:51:21.661
- This somebody I know?
- Your little brother knew him.

01:51:22.541 --> 01:51:25.203
- Rizzo?
- Mm-hmm.

01:51:25.911 --> 01:51:28.106
